title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 of each meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers and top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, salt and sugar to a boil.
Mix cornstarch with a little of the water.
Add to boiling mixture.
Stir in jello and cook until clear; then cool.
Place fresh washed strawberries in a baked pie shell (be sure you have drained them well and lay on paper towels to pat dry).
Pour thickened filling over berries. Refrigerate pie several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Garnish with a whole fresh strawberry with each serving.

title: chocolate cake(the kids favorite)
directions: Melt butter, buttermilk and chocolate in double boiler.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Beat eggs slightly and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cook cake completely!

title: three week slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, chopped onion and celery seed.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand one hour before stirring.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Pour 1/4 cup butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: blueberry cream cheese muffins(10 to 14 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill the cups of a muffin tin with cupcake liners.
Set aside.
In a mixer or processor, whip cream cheese with lemon juice and vanilla extract until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and butter and mix until well blended.

title: olives and mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add all of the olive juice and marinate for 24 hours before serving.

title: winter squash quiche
directions: Bake pastry and keep it warm.
In small skillet, cook the bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper toweling.
Finely crumble and set aside.
Reserve 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion in the warm pastry shell.
In a bowl, combine the eggs, milk, squash, salt, nutmeg and pepper; pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, combine milk and mayonnaise; mix in remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yield: 4 servings (about 3 cups).

title: springerle's
directions: Beat eggs 15 minutes, add sugar and beat 15 minutes more.
Add shortening (butter) continue beating 15 minutes more.
Mix in 7 cups sifted flour; the other 1 cup is used for rolling out the batter.
Add in the baking powder and Anise seeds.
On a floured surface roll out the batter not thin.
Use a Springerle rolling pin.
Cut cookies and let stand over night before baking.
Bake 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Grease cookie sheet.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, cheese, Bisquick and seasonings well in a large bowl.
Pour into a well-greased casserole.
Beat eggs and oil together; pour over zucchini mixture, blending well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Freezes and reheats well.

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and Kool-Aid in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Pour into ice cube trays, small paper cups or frozen pop molds.
Insert wooden sticks at an angle for handles after partially frozen.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy scallops(and sooooo good!)
directions: Wash and drain scallops.
Place single layer in a baking dish or pan.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with parsley, basil and salt. Stir after 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until very thick.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.
Add water, bouillon cubes and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until bouillon is dissolved, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in potato flakes and corn until blended.
Add half and half.
Return to heat.
Heat gently, stirring frequently; do not boil.
Garnish each serving with additional green onion slices, if desired.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: tex mix
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together, bottom layer with chips, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: quick apple pinwheels
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
On greased baking sheet, arrange triangles, bases overlapping, in a complete circle (center of circle should be open with points toward outside).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure all ingredients into a large bowl. Blend well.
Grease a baking pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until done.
Cool.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook Ragu, tomato sauce, cheese, sugar, salt and pepper to taste on stove, stirring continually until it comes to a boil. Brown hamburger, drain; mix into sauce.
Mix spaghetti with sauce. Turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Top with remaining cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add seasonings and dried beef.
Heat to serving temperature.
Great served over baked potatoes or toast or English muffins.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a gallon container.
Put in whole pickles and place in the refrigerator. Ready to use after 2 weeks.

title: ritzy turnips
directions: Prepare, cube and boil turnips 15 to 20 minutes in salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water).
Drain and mash well.
Add shortening, salt, pepper, sugar and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
With same beater, beat yolks until light. Stir yolks gradually into hot turnips.
Fold in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffy and lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: lemon grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in first 9 ingredients at least 4 hours or overnight.
Grill over hot coals, 45 to 60 minutes.
Baste frequently.
Cook until juice is clear and meat is white.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually blend in other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple-orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: asparagus bites
directions: Cut crusts off bread and roll flat with rolling pin.
Spread each piece of bread with the following mixture: Roka cheese, mayonnaise and egg.
Top each with an asparagus spear.
Roll each piece up and dip in melted butter; cut into 3 pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a soup pot, saute garlic in the olive oil for 2 minutes. Add 4 cans of broth and tortellini.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and spinach, bring heat back up to simmer for 5 minutes.
The tortellini absorbs moisture so you might want to add more broth.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese just before serving.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. When done, poke holes in cake with a toothpick. Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake. Then caramel topping over milk. Crush Butterfinger bars and sprinkle on top. After cake has cooled, spread Cool Whip on top. Take remaining candy bar and sprinkle on top for garnish.

title: pink cloud
directions: In large bowl, dissolve Jell-O according to package directions.
Chill until partially set.
With electric beater, whip until soft peaks form.
Dissolve dry milk in water; gradually add to Jell-O, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gradually beat in cranberry sauce until peaks form again.
Put in sherbet glasses; chill or freeze for sherbet.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Drop 1/4 cup of ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 450° for 6 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Slice off top of each potato, scoop out inside and mash.
Add margarine, salt and enough milk to moisten.
Mix and beat until fluffy.
Fill potato shells half full with mashed potatoes on top. (At this point, may be refrigerated overnight.)
Before serving, bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned.
Top with Topper Sauce.

title: mashed potato filling (pa. dutch)
directions: Mash potatoes with milk,
salt and pepper, needs to be a little runny.
Brown onions, celery in crisco in skillet until soft, add bread crumbs to absorb crisco.
Mix onions and celery mixture into potatoes, add eggs.
Stir well and put in baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees 1 hour or until slightly browned.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chopped nuts, in mixer until smooth and creamy.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit tray (strawberries, cantaloupe, honeydew, watermelon, pineapple, apples).

title: mustard sauce for ham
directions: Cook in double boiler for 1/2 hour.
Serve over ham slices.

title: hearthside sandwich
directions: Pull off thin layer from top crust of bread.
Make 6 or more cuts at equal intervals from top to almost bottom of loaf.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, onion, mustard, poppy seed, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Blend well.
Save 3 tablespoons of mixture. Put 2 cheese slices in each slice.
Spread mixture on each slice. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Spread remaining mixture on top and sides of loaf.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and loaf is lightly browned.
Place bacon on top last 10 minutes before finished.

title: marshmallow truffles
directions: Dip 1 marshmallow into melted chocolate turning to coat. Shake off excess chocolate.
Place on a sheet of wax paper, sprinkle with 1 teaspoon pecans.
Repeat with other marshmallows, chocolate and pecans.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 1/2-2 hours or until set.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Wash, core and cook whole cabbage in boiling water until barely tender.
Separate about 8 large leaves from cabbage. Combine beef, rice, onion salt, pepper and paprika.
Place one spoonful of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf; roll up, tucking in ends to make neat compact bundles.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, onion and celery into large enough pot to cover with water by 1 inch.
Bring to boil; simmer 1/2 hour.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix well all wet and dry ingredients.
Roll wienies in plain flour, then dip in mixture.
Fry in deep fat fryer until golden brown.

title: treacle tart
directions: Warm syrup.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
When butter has melted, add milk, lemon rind and beaten egg.
Pour into pastry case.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375° until pastry is cooked and the filling is golden brown.

title: kennebunk pickle(a pioneer recipe)
directions: Chop the vegetables very fine. Add the salt and let stand overnight. Drain. Add the vinegar and brown sugar. Combine the cinnamon, cloves and mustard and tie in a small cheesecloth sack. Boil everything for about 30 minutes. Remove the cheesecloth sack. Pour into sterilized jars.

title: jello ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in
ice
cream until smooth.
Let set for 15 to 25 minutes
before
adding
fruit. Raspberries also can be used.
Double for bigger salad.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together and drop by teaspoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: parmesan corn
directions: Combine cheese, margarine, parsley and salt.
Spread a rounded tablespoonful of mixture on each ear of corn.
Wrap securely in foil.
Place on grill over low to medium coals.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until corn is done.

title: rolled sugar cookie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; add flour, milk and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Roll out; cut and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: orange jello delight
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for approximately 3 hours.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour over rice.
Mix well and refrigerate for several hours.
Combine with green pepper, celery and chicken.
To mold, add 3/4 cup mayonnaise. Pack into large bowl and turn out onto lettuce leaves.
Garnish with avocado.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Add eggs with Karo syrup.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or simmer on low for 30 minutes in saucepan.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs and beat.
Add apples and mix well. Sift flour with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to the apple mixture.
Add vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Pour batter into a loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. This is a nice Christmas cake; takes the place of fruit cake, not as rich.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over bran and all-bran flakes and soak.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 4 eggs, soda, flour and salt. Alternately add 1 quart buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Add dates or raisins if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: tomato zucchini saute
directions: Saute zucchini and minced onion in butter or margarine. Add tomatoes, garlic salt,
oregano
leaves
and black pepper. Saute 5 minutes.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large shallow dish.
Set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain and serve on lettuce.

title: hanson crab
directions: Drain crab.
Chop chestnuts very fine; mix with mayonnaise, soy sauce, chives and crab meat.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: canned venison
directions: Put cut-up venison in roaster.
Add seasonings.
Bake 3 hours in a 300° oven.
Place in jars.
Pressure in canner for 40 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry Jell-O.
Add pineapple, oranges and pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: easy spinach salad
directions: Remove any stems from spinach. Tear into bite-size pieces. Combine spinach, almonds, oranges, mushrooms and bacon bits in large bowl. Toss with desired amount of poppy seed dressing and top with hard-boiled egg.

title: poor man's frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk on stove until paste forms.
Cool.
Beat next four ingredients until mixed. Add flour mixture.
Beat until sugar dissolves.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese, egg, onion and 1/2 teaspoon oregano in a greased baking pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fraternity slush
directions: Boil 2 cups of water; once it is boiling, turn off or remove from heat and put in tea bags.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Mix 7 cups water and sugar, then pour in tea/water.
Add orange juice, lemonade and vodka.
Freeze 24 hours, then serve.

title: spinach souffle quiche
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells; top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 20 hours; drain.
Add chicken broth and heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Melt butter in skillet and saute onion, celery and carrots 3 to 5 minutes.
Add to beans along with potatoes, bay leaf, oregano and black pepper; simmer for another 45 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve and garnish with lemon slices.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk.
Let stand until moistened.
Add eggs and shortening; beat well, then add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar (sifted).
Stir only until combined.
Add extra raisins if wanted.
Fill muffin tins (grease, if not using cupcake papers) 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, about 3 or 4 medium size.
Mash them as to cream.
Add 3 eggs, 2 1/2 cups sugar, salt, margarine, nutmeg, cinnamon, vanilla, lemon flavoring and Pet milk.
Mix all together until smooth.
Add coconut, 1 can flakes or 1 cup from package. Mix all together.
Pour into 2 shells.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of filling comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool, if desired.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add oatmeal and dry ingredients; blend well. Bake at 350° until done in a 9 x 13 pan, greased and floured.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cool before slicing.

title: macadamia snowballs
directions: Cream
butter;	add
flour, rum, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts; mix
by
hand.
Wrap
in plastic and refrigerate 1 hour. Roll in balls;
bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: sunny orange marmalade
directions: Peel oranges and cut rind into thin strips.
Chop pulp, discarding seeds.
Cut lemons into thin slices discarding seeds. Combine orange rind, chopped pulp, lemon slices, and 4 cups water in a large dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover, and chill for 8 hours or overnight.
Combine fruit mixture and sugar and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 1 1/2 hours or until a candy thermometer registers 215 degrees.
Pack hot marmalade into hot sterilized jars filling to 1/2 inch of the top. Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with rings and lids.
These can be processed in boiling water for five minutes, also.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in Dutch oven in butter.
Add ground chuck, seasoned salt, pepper and sugar; brown well.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water; simmer 15 minutes.
Into a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer tomatoes, meat mixture and noodles.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Make sure noodles are well covered by sauce. Cover with aluminum foil; bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut and serve as you would lasagne.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak the Grape-Nuts, sour milk , sugar, egg and oil together for 10 minutes.
Add the flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Bake in 2 small or 1 large pan.
Let rise 20 minutes, then bake at 350°.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over shredded cabbage.
Mix mustard and mayonnaise; mix with cabbage.
Mix vinegar, sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil, then pour over cabbage and mix well. This will keep well in fridge for up to 2 months.

title: breakfast ham and egg casserole
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread slices.
Cut into small cubes.
Combine bread cubes, ham, cheese, salt and pepper; stir well.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in milk.
Add egg mixture to ham mixture, stirring well.
Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: bowl - 'em over salad
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Boil water and butter in a saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and seed all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms ball (approximately 1 minute).
Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth.
Spread batter evenly in bottom of greased glass 9-inch pan.
Have batter touching sides of pan; do not spread up sides.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool slowly away from drafts.
The puff will form a bowl (high on sides and flat in the center).
Great filled with a seafood salad with a mayonnaise base with lemon.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water until the gelatin is dissolved. Add strawberries and stir until thick.
Add the bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.
Spread with sour cream or whipped cream. Then cover with the remaining gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate. Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash, string, trim and cut or break into 1 inch pieces.
Pack into clean jars to within 1/2 inch of top of jar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint.
Fill to within 1/2 inch of top of jar with boiling water.
Put on cap and screw band firmly tight.
Process: pints 20 minutes, quarts 25 minutes, 10 pounds pressure.

title: eggplant szechuan(caution:  spicy hot!)
directions: Cut the eggplant into thumb-sized pieces.
Assemble all the other ingredients.
Heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil and saute the eggplant over medium-low heat.
Keep the skillet covered between stirrings and add 2 tablespoons of water at a time if the eggplant sticks to the pan.

title: marie's barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients.
Use for a good size roast in oven until flakes easily work fork (3 hours?).
Flake.

title: 1994 cannon county 4-h blue ribbon biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut or rub shortening into flour until particles are so fine as coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir in with a fork.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out about 1/2-inch and cut with a floured cutter.
Place biscuits in a greased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: b~b~q meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into meatballs.

title: cutout cookies(serves 36.  makes about 3 dozen.)
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add cream cheese and blend. Add eggs and blend.
Sift together and add dry ingredients.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 400° until light golden, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower divine
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions but until very soft.
Drain.
Place in bowl and add remaining ingredients. Mix and whip well with mixer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cavatina
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the last 3.
Let set.
Boil the 3 types of noodles together until tender; drain.
Layer in a casserole dish with 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese.
Finish with sauce on top.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.
Should be sloppy.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together
and
bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh hot jalapeno salsa
directions: Cook peppers in oil in skillet over medium heat until peppers are lightly browned.
Pour peppers and oil, onions and salt into blender and puree.
If you want milder taste, remove seeds from peppers.
To add tomato taste, may add 5 fresh tomatoes to mixture.

title: pineapple cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, pineapple chunks, carrots, celery and pepper. Toss lightly to mix.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream, honey or sugar, celery seed and salt.
Pour over vegetables and mix carefully.

title: glenn's quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put thin layer of cheese on bottom of crusts.
Beat eggs and slowly blend in cream; add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300°. Cook 35 to 45 minutes more or until toothpick comes out clean. Good reheated the next day.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix above ingredients and let set until congealed (the ones with stars beside them).

title: rio hato hot dish
directions: Brown ground chuck. Add onion, garlic, celery and jalapeno when meat is about half cooked; finish browning and drain. Cook noodles 5 minutes in salted water. Drain. Place soups, sauces and water in blend to mix. Bake, covered, in roasting pan for an hour at 350°.

title: pierogis
directions: Mix together flour, eggs and milk to make soft dough.
(May add 1/4 cup water, if needed.)
On well floured board, roll out dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Fill as for a turnover with sauerkraut, mashed potatoes, cottage cheese or your favorite cheese.
Then drop into boiling water; boil for 15 minutes.
Use a wooden spoon to stir; drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Place drained Pierogis in skillet of onions and butter; heat through until browned.
Serve with shaker cheese on top.

title: holly clusters
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in saucepan.
When mixture bubbles, add food color.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add corn flakes.
Quickly place on cookie sheet by tablespoons.
Add 3 red hots for cherries.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Add to hot water.
By the cup, 1 to 2 teaspoons to 1 cup.
Wonderful at Christmas!

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour with salt, baking powder and soda.
Add alternately sour milk and flour to creamed butter or margarine and flour.
Add nuts or raisins and chopped raw apples.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear angel food cake and add 1/3 Cool Whip. Press in pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and rest of Cool Whip.
Pour over cake. Place strawberries on top. Squeeze 2 packages gel over strawberries. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: red magic meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Form into a loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inches) in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes. Combine the 1/4 cup ketchup with pineapple.
Spoon over loaf. Bake 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt willie's beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve with hot bread and fresh salad.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat milk to boiling point.
While milk is heating, mix together pumpkin, flour, sugar, salt and egg yolks.
Add the boiling milk, beat egg whites and add to the rest.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat gradually to 300° and bake until firm.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Cook 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool one minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Yield:
4 dozen!

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard; cut each wing in half at joint.
On rack in broiler pan, arrange wings.
Broil 6 inches from heat, 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear, turning occasionally.
Transfer to serving platter.
Meanwhile, in 1 qt. saucepan, over medium heat, heat hot pepper sauce and margarine until margarine is melted, stirring often.
Drizzle over wings.
Serve with celery stick and dressing for dipping.

title: poached apples
directions: Bring water, sugar and nutmeg to boil in a large deep skillet. Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced in volume.
Add rum and apples.
Cover and simmer over low heat, 10 to 15 minutes, gently stirring 2 or 3 times until apples are tender.
Remove from heat and stir in raisins.
Serves 4.

title: carrot souffl
directions: Steam or boil carrots until extra soft. Drain well. While carrots are warm, add sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Whip with mixer until smooth. Add flour and mix well. Whip eggs and add to flour mixture; blend well. Add softened margarine to mixture and blend well. Pour mixture into baking dish about half full, as the souffl will rise. Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until top is a light golden brown. Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar over top before serving. Serves 10.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix and chill at serving time.
Add 1 large bag of crushed Fritos.

title: white sauce(diabetic recipe)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, salt and Worcestershire sauce; blend thoroughly.
Add skim milk; cook until slightly thickened.

title: coconut mist cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking powder and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites quickly and thoroughly.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 375° for about 25-30 minutes.
Frost with "Coconut Frosting Tinted Pink".
(I first made this cake 51 years ago!)

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Use filling of your choice (chicken salad, ham salad, etc.)

title: czechoslovakia cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg yolks.
Add walnuts and flour. Divide in half.
Roll between wax paper.
Put layer on bottom of 15 x 10-inch sheet pan.
Spread with filling or jelly, if desired. Cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma potatoes
directions: Melt bacon drippings into large heavy skillet.
Slice enough potatoes to fill skillet full.
Add a medium-size onion, chopped coarse.
Cook over medium heat, stirring with spatula and letting potatoes brown.
Cover skillet.
Add hot water as needed, in small amounts.
Cook until potatoes are done.
This is so good for breakfast with sausage or bacon and cream gravy and biscuits.

title: curried lima bean casserole
directions: Note:
This can be assembled several hours ahead of time, but add 10 minutes to cooking time.

title: christmas or valentine's punch
directions: Mix well and serve.
A delicious and different punch.

title: my mom's chocolate cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add sugar mixture and sour milk alternately to the flour and mix well.
Pour into two 8-inch greased and floured round pans or a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until it tests done.
Let cool before removing from the pans onto wire rack to finish cooling.

title: never fail quiche
directions: Add flour to beaten eggs.
Then mix in rest of ingredients. Pour into prepared pie shell and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Another vegetable can be substituted for the spinach.

title: june's tuna salad
directions: Cook pasta and toss with French dressing.
Set aside until cool.
Cut up other ingredients and toss in bowl with tuna and salad dressing.
Let set overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Clean and hull strawberries.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add water and lemon juice.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook and stir until slightly thickened and clear, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in strawberries.
Turn into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or until set. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Drain pineapple; squeeze out with hands. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Serve as a dip, a ball with crackers or a sandwich spread.

title: blueberry muffins(for 12 muffins)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries. Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin cups or cupcake holders. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.

title: party rye sausage snacks
directions: Brown meats, drain and remove from pan. Melt cheese in the same pan.
Add spices to melted cheese and mix.
Mix meats with cheese.
Spread on party rye bread and bake on cookie sheets for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add bananas (which have been crushed with fork until soft).
Alternate with sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into a well-greased long loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot sausage cheese puffs
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick with a fork.
Add water; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Freeze and bag.
Yield: 120 puffs.
To reheat: 10 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch casserole with aluminum foil.
Place steak in pan.
Add butter, onion soup, bell pepper and drained tomatoes. Shake together in a jar soup, salt, tomato juice and cornstarch. Pour over steak.
Close foil tightly over steak.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese
directions: Mix the flour, oleo and walnuts.
Press in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Form into 2 or 3 balls.
Roll in nuts.

title: toffee
directions: Butter square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Spread pecans in pan. Heat brown sugar and margarine to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Immediately spread evenly over pecans.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Cover pan with cookie sheet.
Let stand about 1 minute or until chips soften.
Spread softened chocolate over candy.
While hot, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add cold water and boiling water, 2 cups flour and the yeast mixture.
Beat well and add remaining flour.
Mix well.
May refrigerate and use as needed or let rise until double.
Work down and make out into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400°.

title: relish
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Grind night before. Add salt.
Drain in the morning.
Add peppers (red and green), sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Heat all together 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: red ribbon punch
directions: Double this to make a punch bowl full.
Mix all ingredients, adding sherbet last.

title: poor man's meal
directions: Patty meat out and place in a cake pan.
Cut carrots, potatoes, onion and squash up into round slices and place on top. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: meat and potatoes for potluck
directions: Fry suet and brown hamburger.
Season with sage and bay leaf. Cut potatoes and onions thin and arrange in layers alternately in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over layers.
Bake in a 350° oven (moderate oven) until potatoes are tender.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour oatmeal and margarine in mixing bowl.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand for 20 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat together.
(Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.)
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly and spread with topping.

title: russia tea
directions: Mix well and store in tight jar.
Use 2 1/2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a simmer, stirring well.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: creamed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Put in baking dish, then mix the remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over the top of potatoes.
Bake a few minutes slowly.
To keep sweet potatoes from turning dark, use 1/2 cup crushed pineapple or lemon juice.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: Combine beans, bourbon, brown sugar, coffee powder, mustard and lemon juice.
Turn into individual bean pots or casseroles (I used a regular casserole; but I doubled recipe).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes four servings.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, crushed soda crackers, corn, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in
water;
remove from heat.
Gradually add butter, cheese
and
Worcestershire sauce.	Gradually stir 1/4 cup grits into eggs;
then add the rest of the grits, stirring well. Pour mixture
in
slightly	greased
casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish
with sliced mushrooms and parsley. Good stuff.

title: chicken breast hobo meal
directions: You will need 4 foil sheets, 11 x 14.

title: fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off heat and stir in candy bar, chocolate bits, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Stir until all ingredients are melted and thoroughly mixed together.
Put in buttered pan.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pie plate or quiche dish. Pour and spread chili on top of cream cheese. Top with shredded cheese.
Heat in microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes, covered, or in a regular oven at 350° until ingredients are bubbling. Serve hot and use nacho chips for dipping.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with thawed lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in a graham cracker crumb crust.
Chill.

title: pfeffernuesse (pepper nut) cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda in large bowl.
Beat sugar with oleo with electric mixer at high speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, then spices and corn syrup, blending well.
At low speed, stir in flour, 1 cup at a time, until well mixed.
Cover dough; refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into nugget size pieces.
Roll each piece in flour.
Dip into flour and then roll in bread crumbs.
At this point the nuggets may be pan fried in a small amount of oil or baked.
Be sure to turn over halfway through cooking.
Cook until golden brown.

title: split pea soup(makes 3 quarts; 10 to 12 servings)
directions: In a large soup pot or Dutch oven, soak rinsed peas in 2 cups cold water for 1 to 2 hours. Add remaining 8 cups water, celery tops, onion, garlic and ham bone. Simmer 2 hours. Remove and discard celery, onion and ham bone.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef separately.
Return to skillet; add seasonings and cheese.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on bread. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy oven roast beef
directions: Use a roasting pan or Dutch oven.
Line with aluminum foil. Put roast in pan.
Mix salt, pepper and onion soup mix and spread on top of roast.
Pour water over roast slowly so as not to wash off the seasoning.
Cover with foil.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 1 to 2 hours.
Save gravy to serve over rice.

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix well.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or with crackers.

title: chilled blueberry cheese dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine graham crackers, sugar and melted butter.
Mix and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; a little up on sides also. Bake at 350° about 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: "ma" sparks cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out. Slice and bake at 350°.

title: corned beef and noodle bake
directions: Cook and drain noodles; put noodles and cut up corned beef into shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion around.
Mix together milk, soup and add on top grated cheese and crushed potato chips or crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute bacon until crisp and drain off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onion, green pepper and okra.
Cook until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Stir in rice, broth and seasoning. Bring to a boil and reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add tomato and fluff lightly. Replace lid and allow to stand about 10 minutes.

title: pickled heart or tongue
directions: Cook heart and tongue in boiling water until done; let cool. Pack in clean jar(s).
Cover with sliced onion and garlic cloves. Add other brine ingredients to same water and bring to a boil. Pour boiling hot liquid over heart and tongue.
Seal.

title: scottish scones(this recipe is from early nova scotia)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with a pie dough blender.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients until you have a soft dough.
Add raisins.
Roll out dough on a floured board to 1 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in rounds with a glass or cookie cutter. Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and jam.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Beat together milk and puddings; layer over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and grated chocolate bar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar together; add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and salt.
Chill for 1 hour, roll and cut out your favorite shapes.

title: hog back pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a greased skillet.
Arrange chops in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour apple juice over chops; sprinkle with raisins and salt.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn chops.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat sugar and cooking oil until blended.
Beat eggs and vanilla; combine with sugar mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients. Roll into 1-inch balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: mushrooms baked in foil
directions: Rinse, pat dry and trim fresh mushrooms.
Place in center of a sheet of foil.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bring edges of foil up over mushroom mixture.
Crimp seal.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until cooked.

title: party cheese crisps
directions: Mix together, roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and pat flat with fork.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 7 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: apple-spice cake
directions: Put all ingredients together and beat well.
Bake in a Bundt pan or tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat. Add next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper. Simmer at least 1 hour. Combine cottage cheese with parsley, salt and pepper. In large oblong pan, layer 1/4 meat sauce, 3 lasagna noodles, 1/2 the cottage cheese and 8 ounces Mozzarella. Repeat, ending with meat sauce, noodles and remaining meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Prepare the next 3 ingredients; set aside until ready to use.
Grease a large iron skillet.
Heat, then sprinkle very thin layer of creamed corn mixture in hot skillet.
Let brown lightly.
Pour half batter in skillet; sprinkle half cheese over batter.
Next, add the meat, then the cheese, then onion and pepper.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cut up chicken parts
directions: Do not salt.
Soup has enough salt.
You may add pepper.

title: supper corn chowder
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and pour off drippings, returning 3 tablespoons to pan.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer a minute or two.
Crumble bacon over chowder.
Top each serving with butter.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Put blueberries in deep greased baking dish and sprinkle them with the 1/4 cup sugar and the lemon juice.
Cream the butter and brown sugar and add quick oats.
Spread over blueberries and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Remove from water.
Stir in shortening and salt.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored. Gradually beat in sugar.
Continue beating until very thick.
Add chocolate mixture, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir pineapple and pudding mix together.
Blend in Cool Whip. Add marshmallows.
Chill.
A delicious low-fat, lo-cal salad.

title: halloween party witches brew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan; heat over low heat until ready to serve.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Ladle brew into serving cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into a 9-inch pie crust that has been baked at least 5 minutes in the oven.
Bake slowly at 300°.
For two pies, use 5 eggs and double the rest of the ingredients.

title: stuffed mushrooms with crabmeat
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Remove and finely chop mushroom stems. In medium bowl, combine chopped stems, soup mix, crabmeat, sour cream, bread crumbs, dill, hot pepper sauce and pepper; set aside. On lightly greased baking sheet arrange mushroom caps and fill with crabmeat mixture; brush with butter.
Bake 15 minutes or until tender.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Put 1/2 of mixture in mold.
Chill until firm and top with a thin layer of sour cream.
Add remaining jello mixture and chill for approximately 2 hours.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter.
Add eggs; beat well. Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to butter mixture gradually.
Spread thin in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cookie pan. Cook at 375° for about 14 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: pineapple crowned fruit pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and sugar.
Stir in melted butter until well blended.
Pat into 9-inch pie plate.
Dip bananas in lemon juice (to maintain color).
Arrange banana slices in bottom of pie.
Arrange sliced strawberries on top.
In saucepan, add cornstarch to undrained pineapple.
Cook and stir over medium high heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add vanilla. Cool at room temperature.
Spoon into pie.
Chill several hours. Sprinkle with nuts.
Easy to make and very festive on a hot night.

title: rice and almond
directions: Saute almonds and chopped celery in oleo.
Add chicken broth and bring to boil.
Add rice; cover and turn burner off.
Let mixture sit covered for at least 20 minutes.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Combine beer and chicken in 3-quart saucepan; stir over medium-high heat until stock is dissolved.
Add carrot, celery and onion; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Blend 1 1/2 cups milk with flour in medium bowl.
Gradually stir flour mixture into soup, blending well.
Add remaining milk and cook, stirring until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Blend in cheese slowly, stirring until melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve immediately.

title: one-pot turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion in butter in large heavy pot until tender.
Add broth, water and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti gradually so liquid continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until tender.
Add more water, if needed.
Set aside 1/4 of pimento for garnish.
Add remaining ingredients to spaghetti, cover and heat for 3 minutes.
Turn into serving dish. Garnish with pimento and parsley.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift dry ingredients together and add, alternating with milk; beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon into a greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes and turn onto a cake plate.

title: peppermint frosting
directions: Blend powdered sugar with enough cream to make frosting of spreading consistency.
Add extracts and mix together.
Add red food coloring to color.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Add chopped onion to boiling macaroni to soften.
Drain.
In a bowl mix tuna, cheese sauce mix, can of soup and 2 ounces of grated cheese.
Add noodles and onion. Mix well.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with the remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes

title: cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread together and chill before using.
Trim bread and spread with mixture.
Cut into 3 strips for parties.
Can also be molded and served with cocktail crackers.

title: southern style chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover whole chicken with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Debone chicken.
Measure 4 cups chicken broth; add soups and bring to a boil.
Cut 12 tortillas into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop into boiling broth and soup mixture. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle recipe with 1 teaspoon black pepper.
Add chicken.
Stir thoroughly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; then add raisins, walnuts, pineapple, coconut, dates, soda, baking powder and flour.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in covered pan with about 1-inch of water about 10 minutes.
Remove and reserve water.
Take leaves apart carefully.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon loosely into each leaf. Roll up each one, folding towards center.
Place in small roaster or large casserole dish.
The center of cabbage can be cut in 6 sections and placed on top. Add reserved liquid. Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
About the last 15 minutes of cooking, add 1 large can tomato paste or tomato soup and a large can of tomatoes.

title: grandma connely's pineapple salad
directions: Reserve 1 cup of juice from pineapple tidbits when drained. Mix together pineapple juice, sugar, flour and eggs.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Let mixture cool.
Mix together pineapple tidbits, marshmallows and pecans.
Add cooled pineapple juice mixture.
Stir in 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: spaghetti and tomatoes
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender. Drain. Saute chopped onions in skillet with a little bacon grease. Add spaghetti and crushed tomatoes. Let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Place frozen bread dough on well-greased baking sheets. Grease top of each loaf.
Let stand, covered, for 2 hours or until thawed.
Do not let rise.
Brown ground beef and sausage with onion and green pepper in skillet, stirring frequently; drain. Cool.
Press dough with greased hands over surface of baking sheets.
Layer with ground beef mixture and cheese.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place seam side down on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: basic "scratch" tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large heavy pot over medium-low heat.
Add garlic and cook until it colors slightly but does not burn, 3 to 4 minutes.
Watch the garlic carefully as it cooks, to be sure it does not burn.
Once garlic starts to color, it cooks very fast. Remove from heat and carefully stir in the tomatoes and wine. Return the pot to medium heat.
Stir in the parsley, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately or cool and store, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 2 days or freeze the sauce for later use.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: swedish meatballs(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into bite size balls; brown and drain.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together ingredients and stir well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate (boiled) cookies
directions: Put margarine, sugar, milk, cocoa and vinegar in a heavy saucepan.
Stir and let come to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Mix well and drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Can be poured into pan and cut into squares.
No baking necessary.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Put grated cheese in baking pan.
Combine soup, sour cream and onion and pour over potatoes.
Pour butter over top, then top with corn flakes that have been rolled with a rolling pin and cheese. Bake in oven until cheese melts and potatoes cook a little more.

title: poor man's shrimp
directions: Cut fillets into strips.
Place fillets in rapidly boiling, salted water.
Return to boil.
Drain.
Ice immediately.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: easy skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef and onions in a large skillet.
Pour off any fat and stir in cooled macaroni, tomato sauce, corn, chili powder and salt.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place mixture on top of cream cheese filling and bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Butter Bundt pan; place frozen rolls in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over and around rolls.
Let raise overnight.
Bake in morning in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion.
Add hamburger meat and brown.
Add chili mix and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Cook celery and onion; drain.
Mix mushroom soup, crushed crackers and cheese whip together.
Mix cooked broccoli, celery and onion together.

title: beef stew
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine flour and pepper.
Dredge meat in flour mixture, reserving the excess. Cook meat, 3/4 cup onion and reserved flour mixture in oil in a Dutch oven over low heat until meat is lightly browned.
Add water and next five ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in potato, 1 cup carrot and 1 cup onion.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add peas and cook 10 minutes. Yields 6 cups. Preparation time is 2 hours.

title: silliness putty
directions: Mix with hands.
When the mixture clumps, pour it hand to hand, kneading it and adding the liquid starch until the texture and consistency desired is reached.

title: delicious applesauce fruitcake
directions: Mix as any other fruitcake.
Bake until firm.
Use pan of water under cake and piece of Reynolds Wrap on top of cake.
Take off Reynolds Wrap and let brown slightly.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Cut up the cucumbers to the size you want.
Mix all the remaining ingredients and pour mixture over the cucumbers.
Put them in the refrigerator.
It needs no boiling.
This will keep for months.

title: cereal bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil; add peanut butter, vanilla and cereal.
Stir.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips with 1 tablespoon peanut butter.
Spread on bars.

title: banana fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Drain pineapple. Add syrup and cold water to make 3/4 cup.
Add to gelatin.
Chill until very thick.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in pineapple, banana and marshmallows.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hello dolly squares
directions: Melt butter in long cake pan. Add individual items in order listed, by sprinkling graham cracker crumbs over butter, then chocolate chips, nuts and coconut. Drizzle condensed milk over the mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling, then crushed pineapple into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with icing.

title: salad and poppy seed dressing
directions: Arrange lettuce on salad plates.
Top with rest of ingredients.
Drizzle with dressing and garnish with grapes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth. Combine celery soup, chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Layer chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top of soup mixture.
Heat the broth saved from the chicken and butter. Pour over all.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together in a bowl.
Add egg and milk; stir until well mixed.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into hot oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs and add the milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Mix in flour and beat.
The butter will get cold, so it will look a little lumpy.
Melt 1 teaspoon of butter in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Pour approximately 1/3 cup (or a little more if your skillet is larger) into the pan.
Tip the pan so the batter covers the bottom in a thin layer.
Fry until slightly brown on one side and flip to brown on the other.
Keep warm in a 250° oven between layers of towel on a platter.
Serve with butter, cane sugar, powdered sugar or lingonberry butter.

title: kaiserschmarrn(the emperor's omelet)
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until light and pale.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to egg mixture alternately with the milk, beating well after each addition.
The batter should be smooth.
Add raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold into batter.

title: ever-so-easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend in dry ingredients.
Pour batter into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
I have also baked this in 2 loaf pans, reducing baking time.

title: mother's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until filling begins to thicken; reduce heat to 350°.
Pie is done when knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
This is a Thanksgiving "must" in my family.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, beating until well blended. Fold topping into mixture.
Ladle into pie crust; sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze until firm before serving.

title: my "best" oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda and oats.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins.

title: jacob's meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, soup mix and egg.
Make small meatballs.
Drop into boiling water and cook until done; drain. Mix chili sauce and jelly.
Put meatballs and smokies in baking dish.
Top with sauce and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Can substitute barbecue sauce.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together. Spread into bottom of crust. Add Cool Whip to top of this. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces.
Squeeze one fresh lemon over pieces.
In plastic bag, combine flour, salt, paprika and add chicken pieces and shake.
Brown pieces in oil.
Combine brown sugar, broth and bitters.
Put cooked rice in bottom of pan; top with chicken pieces and pour broth on top.
Top with one sliced lemon.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Bring water to boil and add oatmeal.
Cover tightly; remove from heat.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream together butter and sugars, then add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Mix in oats.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Slowly add to oat mixture.
Mix well and pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until middle is done.

title: summer vegetable salad
directions: In heavy pan, heat oil and cook garlic with lemon juice, wine, thyme, and salt and pepper to taste for 5 minutes. Add corn and simmer for about 3 minutes.
Combine all.
Refrigerate so flavors blend.
Serve cold or room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix well.
Place in 10-inch glass pie dish.
Press down with wax paper.
Great gift.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 4 eggs; add a cup of oil and sour cream. Beat well. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together well. Take 1 cup of batter and mix with brown sugar mixture. Pour 1/2 of batter into a pan. Use the brown sugar mix and spoon it over the other batter. Take the rest of the batter and pour it over. Using a knife, swirl the two contents well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Use cream cheese icing to spread over hot cake.

title: hamburger casserole(a family favorite!)
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion and seasonings.
Drain fat and place meat mixture in bottom of casserole; cover with the tomato soup.
Layer string beans over soup and then top casserole with the mashed potatoes.
Top with some butter and slices of American cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: You put sugar and cold water and hot water on it and cook it on the stove and then you eat it.

title: glaze for ribs
directions: Baste and charbroil ribs 20 minutes on one side, 10 minutes on the other side, 20 minutes glazing.
Total 50 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix up.
Make a ball.
Push with fork.
Bake 375 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: stromboli(for 1)
directions: Roll bread onto a 10 x 13-inch rectangle pan.
In center third, layer ingredients in order given.
Fold the two outer thirds over the center.
Sprinkle cookie sheet with a light dusting of cornmeal.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Combine broccoli and boiling water; cover and simmer until tender, drain.
Chop broccoli to bite size.
Arrange in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup and milk, stir.
Pour 1/2 over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Top with remaining soup.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Scatter evenly over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chili sauce(salsa)
directions: Note:
For salsa, add jalapeno peppers to taste.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls and place toothpicks in each. Freeze until ready to dip.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine soup, water, mustard and pepper; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook, over low heat, 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often.
Serve with rice.

title: squash supreme casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water.
Drain well and mash. Add grated carrot, soup, sour cream and green chilies.
Mix stuffing and melted butter.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole with half of buttered stuffing.
Pour in squash mixture.
Top with other half of buttered stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: mexican dip
directions: In crock-pot, add beans, picante sauce and cheese.
Start to cook on High.
Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning only (no water).
Mix and add to crock-pot.
Cook low for 2 to 3 hours.
Add tomato last hour of cooking.
Serve with corn chips.

title: dirt cake(flowerpot cake)
directions: Blend together the margarine and cream cheese. Add the powdered sugar.
Combine the pudding and milk and add to above. Fold in the Cool Whip.
(Place in refrigerator until crumbs are ready).
Put the cookies in blender or food processor until crumbs.
Put a layer of Oreo crumbs in bottom of plastic flowerpot, then a layer of mixture, etc.
End with Oreo crumbs on top.
Place silk flower in pot.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pots (plastic flowerpots).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Mix in dry ingredients
and
nuts.
Bake
in 2 prepared loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients and top with salad dressing spread over to edge of pan.
Sprinkle sugar on top, then cheese, then bacon crumbled on top.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Prepare coarse or fine bread crumbs.
Empty crumbs into a large bowl with celery seed, salt, pepper, sage and thyme.
In pot melt margarine with onion and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Stir constantly.
Pour margarine and onion onto bread mixture. Boil water. Then mix water into bread mixture until mixture consistency looks moist.
Pour or place mixture into 9-inch square pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pink cream dessert
directions: Spoon ice crem into blender.
Add all other ingredients, except maraschino cherries.
Cover and blend until smooth (only a few seconds).
Stir in chopped maraschino cherries.
Pour into 4 wine glasses.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chopped apple dessert
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and butter or oil.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Add diced apples and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat over 450 degrees. Place ingredients in large bag, shake well, or just mix in bowl.
Place in shallow baking dish. Bake, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until tender and brown.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until it boils. Mixture will slowly thicken. Cook for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly until thick. Pour over hot, buttered biscuits.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with a spoon, mixing well. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch or square baking dish. Cover with strips of Velveeta cheese. Combine crumbled Ritz crackers with melted margarine and sprinkle on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken 'n dumplings (crock-pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except biscuits, in slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours. Thirty minutes before serving, tear biscuit dough into 1-inch pieces. Add to your slow cooker, stirring gently. Cover and cook on high for an additional 30 minutes or until biscuits are fluffed up and cooked through.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beating at medium speed, add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Begin and end with flour mixture just until blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour in 8-inch greased Bundt pan, tube pan or bread pan.
Bake at 325° for about an hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before serving.

title: krispy lunch slices
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and pickling salt.
Let stand 3 plus hours, then drain.
Combine sugar, mustard seed, turmeric and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Add to first mixture. Heat thoroughly.
Do Not Boil!
Place in jars and seal. SWEET PICKLES FROM DILLS

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over low heat.
Cool. Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese.
Add 1 1/4 cups sugar gradually; cream until fluffy.
Blend 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat 2 eggs and remaining cup sugar until thick.
Add baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in chocolate, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and nuts. Spread half the chocolate batter in a greased 8-inch square pan. Top with cheese mixture.
Spoon remaining chocolate batter over top.
Zig-zag knife through batter to give a marbleized effect. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheesy microwave potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes with skins in a medium size microwave-safe bowl.
Add sliced onion, bacon bits, salt and butter; pour water over potatoes.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes until tender, then add slices of cheese.
Let melt.
Serve hot!

title: mock blintz rolls
directions: Cut crusts of bread off and roll out flat.
Spread each slice with cheese and roll up.
Dip into butter and in cinnamon and sugar.
Chill and cut into bite sized pieces and freeze.
Heat at 400° for 10 minutes.
Do not defrost before baking.

title: fresh vegetable medley
directions: Cut squash and pepper into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Cool slightly, then add marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until cold.
Cut into bars.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Tree and kill a good sized possum.
Skin possum and remove glands and insides.
Clean good.
Scrape clean and scald in boiling water.
Salt and pepper inside and out.
Make a mixture of bread crumbs, applesauce and chestnuts, using equal amounts of each.
Stuff possum with this mixture.
Cover with sweet potatoes and one cup of water and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Bake in butter and baste often.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
In mixing bowl, mix eggs, cheese, sausage and bacon.
Put into baked pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Layer the broccoli spears and chicken in baking dish.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Spoon over the chicken.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Cover with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Clean and prepare fruit.
Set 3 cups fruit aside.
In saucepan, simmer 1 cup fruit and 2/3 cups of water for 3 minutes. Add sugar and cornstarch and remaining 1/3 cup of water.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Put fresh fruit in prebaked pie shell. Pour glaze mixture over fruit all the way to edges.
Chill.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured jumbo fluted mold pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and cracker crumbs.
Pat in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar together for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Layer sliced bananas, cover with pineapple and top with whipped cream. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes a very large cake.

title: golden gate tamale pie
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil slowly until tender.
Add meat and brown quickly.
Add remaining vegetables, olives and seasonings and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir corn meal and salt into boiling water and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter and cook over hot water 20 minutes.
Line bottom and sides of two-quart casserole with corn meal mixture.
Pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: spicy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets, or spray with Pam.
Combine cake mix, egg whites, oats, raisins and oil in a large bowl; mix until well blended.
Drop from rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes. Cool for 1 minute on sheets, then remove to cooling rack.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make jello and chill just until it begins to gel.
Poke holes in top of baked cake.
Fill holes with jello on top of cake.
Chill until set.
Spread pie filling over cake and top with Cool Whip.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers, margarine, sugar and milk in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, covered.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: caramel-chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/4 cup milk over medium heat.
Mix dry cake mix, butter, remaining milk and nuts.
Spread half of this dough in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes; remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut over baked layer.
Drizzle caramel mixture over chocolate chips and coconut.
Drop remaining dough by teaspoons onto caramel layer and spread evenly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until cake is slightly dry to the touch.

title: dreamy apricot mold
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit.
Set aside to cool.
Beat condensed milk and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Next, fold in nuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Serves 20.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Heat next 3 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until warm, not hot.
Pour warm liquid over flour mixture.
Blend at low speed 1 minute, then at medium speed 2 minutes.
By hand, stir in 1 cup additional whole wheat flour and 4 to 4 1/2 cups all-purpose flour.
Knead on floured surface about 5 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl. Cover and let rise 45 to 60 minutes until light and doubled.
Punch down dough.
Divide in half.
Shape each half into a loaf by rolling the dough to a 14 x 7-inch rectangle.
Starting with 7-inch side, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place in greased loaf pans. Cover and let rise 40 to 45 minutes, until light and doubled.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when lightly tapped.
Depending on oven, may have to loosely cover with aluminum the last 15 minutes or so.
Remove from pans immediately.
Cool on wire rack before slicing.

title: creamy refrigerator pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Add milk and lemon juice. Mix well. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into the crust. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or until set. Top with pie filling. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: white meat loaf with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover tomatoes with water.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from water and chop.
Mix tomatoes with remaining ingredients.
Season with pepper and cayenne pepper to taste.
Place in a nonstick loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until juices run clear when a knife is inserted into the center.

title: candied yams
directions: Combine yams, egg, sugar, milk, margarine, vanilla and 1/2 cup pecans in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a 9-inch square casserole. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup pecans and marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Heat oil in pot.
Add beef, a third at a time, and brown on all sides.
Remove as browned.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Place in large baking dish.
Top each with onion and then lemon slice.
Put brown sugar and catsup on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake additional 1/2 hour, basting occasionally.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine salmon with next 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours. Combine nuts and parsley. Shape salmon mixture into balls. Roll in nut mixture. Chill well. Serve with crackers.

title: lemon-blueberry fluff
directions: In large bowl dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in lemon peel, lemon juice and 3/4 cup cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Add unbeaten egg whites to gelatin mixture.
Beat with electric mixer until mixture is light and fluffy, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 8 (5-ounce) custard cups.
Chill until firm. (Slight separation into layers may occur.)

title: grandma's stew
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet; drain.
Place beef and onions in a stew pot.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces; pour into beef.
Peel and cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Pour potatoes into pot.
Add salt and pepper; cook for 1 hour, covered, on low to medium heat.
Add kidney beans; cook until potatoes are tender. If mixture does not have enough water, you may add a small can of tomato paste with water.
Water can be added during cooking as potatoes cook.

title: lowbush cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Combine orange juice and grated rind with well beaten egg.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients and mix just enough to moisten. Carefully fold in chopped nuts and cranberries.

title: betty jo's fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, salt and cocoa until a soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
Add butter and peanut butter and beat with mixer until mixture gets thick.
Add nuts and marshmallows. Spread in a shallow pan and cool.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and place in 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesy tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat the oil or butter in a medium saucepan.
Add the flour to the pan; stir until well blended.
Add the milk and chicken broth, whisking constantly to blend. Continue whisking as the sauce thickens and comes to a boil.

title: garlic parmesan bread
directions: Mix butter and garlic.
Cut loaf into 1-inch thick, without cutting all the way through.
Spread the garlic butter over the bread.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Place loaf on microproof rack or on paper towels.
Cook on High 1 to 2 minutes or until bread is heated through.

title: maggie's taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Add chopped onion, kidney beans and chopped tomatoes.
Stir in Catalina dressing.
Just before serving, add head of lettuce (broken up), and toss with Fritos.

title: wassail
directions: Use this ratio for the quantity you wish to make.
Place spices and orange in small cloth bag.
After doing so, simmer for several hours.
Serve hot.
