title: 7 dry bean soup
directions: Use at least 7 varieties of beans (Great Northern, navy, black turtle, pinto, red, pink and kidney, yellow and green split peas). Rinse beans; place in large kettle and cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water and ham or sausage.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer another 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper as desired. Yields 2 quarts.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Cut soft margarine through until cake mix is crumbly.
Pour peaches in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar over peaches.
Spread cake mix over top of peaches by hand.
Bake at 350° until cake is brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; chill.
Peel and coarsely shred (1 1/2 cups).
Add onion, salt and dash of pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in 8-inch skillet.
Put potatoes in pan, leaving 1 inch space around the edge.
Brown about 9 minutes.
Reduce heat, if necessary; turn.
Brown about 5 minutes longer, or until golden brown.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix 5 minutes. Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar (optional).

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and let stand at room temperature for 8 hours.
Stir well occasionally.
May be kept in refrigerator approximately 6 months.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening.
Save 3/4 cup of the mixture for top crumbs.
To remainder, add baking powder, eggs, soda, sour milk and cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: *Note:
To make festive orange juice ice cubes, simply fill ice trays with orange juice, then freeze.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix together, bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost.

title: bonbons
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and milk.
Add coconut and nuts and mix well.
Roll into walnut size balls and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in top of double boiler over hot water.
With a toothpick dip refrigerated balls into chocolate.
Freezes well.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add potatoes, hot water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until done.
Add hot milk.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Combine cooked hamburger and other ingredients in crock-pot. Heat until smooth.

title: creole pralines
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 225° or about 20 minutes after boiling starts.
Add pecans and continue cooking to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat.
Beat well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Dry until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: yum dumbs
directions: Stir 1 cup Karo syrup and 1 cup sugar over low heat until it bubbles over.
Add 1 cup peanut butter; stir.
Add 6 cups Rice Krispies.
Take off heat and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup butterscotch chips. Spread over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight; cut in squares.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a saucepan, bring butter, cocoa and water to a boil on the stove (or in a microwave-safe dish, microwave until boiling).

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven while oven is heating to 350°.

title: creamy pesto tomato rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat the tomato juice to a boil.
Stir in the rice.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and has absorbed the tomato juice. Pour whipping cream into a 10 inch skillet.
Add rice and cook over medium heat until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat and stir in the pesto.
Serve as a side dish with pork, chicken or fish.

title: spiced raisin pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cardamom and nutmeg. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the flour mixture over the raisins, mixing well. Set aside.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to butter and sugar mixture. Beat until fluffy. Stir in raisins and mix until evenly blended.
Turn into a 6-cup capacity well-greased tube cake pan, 8 to 10-inches in diameter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jane's pear bread
directions: *If yogurt is used, add 2 tablespoons water.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk, beating according to package directions. Add sour cream and half of topping.
Mix well.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers.
Pour pudding over each layer.
Put remaining whipped topping on top.
Sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers or toasted pecans.
Chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, seeds, raisins, crumbled bacon and red cabbage.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over and toss.
Let set for an hour.
You may want to make more dressing.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Chop the onions very fine and brown. Add the ground beef. Cook.
Add the water, ketchup, paprika, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
If not thick enough for personal taste, add cornstarch. Should be very hot.

title: "chix" cheese ball
directions: Mix everything together except nuts.
Shape into balls.
Roll into nuts.
Refrigerate.
Goes with any flavor cracker.

title: breakfast fruit and rice pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over rice and fruit. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and serve hot or make ahead by baking for 30 minutes and reheating just before serving.
Garnish with peaches or banana slices, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mushroom pate
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms in butter; drain well.
Place cream cheese and mushrooms in blender or processor.
Add garlic salt. Place in mold sprayed with Pam or form in a ball.
Garnish with parsley and mushrooms.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: In greased 8-inch square pan, layer 4 slices bread, slices of Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 cup chili sauce and all the broccoli. Repeat layers of bread, cheese and chili sauce.
Combine milk, eggs, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or bake immediately in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Beat together cooking oil, 2 cups sugar and eggs.
Stir in 1 cup chopped nuts (optional), vanilla and apple.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir all together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Mix first 6 ingredients. Top with nuts or coconut.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Can be kept in refrigerator one week.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: Layer 1:
Mix and pat first 3 ingredients into bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla to flour mixture.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Flatten out biscuits by hand into circles.
Add one tablespoon tomato sauce to each biscuit.
Bake for 10 minutes until brown.
Cook 1/2 pound ground beef.
Take off fat and add salt and oregano.
Put mixture on biscuit.
Add desired grated cheese.
Turn oven to 325° and bake until cheese melts (about 5 minutes).

title: tailgate tire pie
directions: Coarsely chop 10 cookies; set aside.
Finely roll 26 cookies. Combine cookie crumbs and margarine or butter; press evenly onto bottom and sides of 9- inch pie plate.
Refrigerate.
Stir marshmallows and milk in 2 quart saucepan over medium heat until melted and smooth.
Cool completely.
Gently fold 2 cups whipped cream into cool marshmallow mixture; save remaining whipped cream for garnish.
Fold in chopped cookies.
Spoon into prepared cookie crumb piecrust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Cut into eight slices.
Garnish each with whipped cream and set cookie on end into whipped cream to resemble a tire.

title: "easy" italian cream cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Fold in the coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake according to directions on box or until lightly browned and cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: fudge brownie fingers
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and stir.
Add melted butter and chocolate.
Mix flour, salt and nutmeats.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and stir until well blended, but do not beat.
Pour into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into 2-inch fingers.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Soften onion in margarine.
Add 2 cups cooked broccoli, mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook rice or prepare Minute rice. Add to rest of mixture.
Stir and place in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° to 375° until crumbs are brown.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In a bowl with a fork, beat cheese until smooth.
Add 1 cup of the pecans and remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in remaining cup of pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. Freezes well.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck with 1/2 package of fajita mix and 2 tablespoons water. Smooth refried beans over bottom of casserole dish, then add cooked macaroni and Ro-Tel. Spread ground chuck over top, then sprinkle cheese over hot meat to melt.
Serve with shredded lettuce, onions and tortilla chips.
Easy and fast.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch butter pan with whole graham crackers.
Combine pudding mix and milk, beat until set; fold in whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on crackers, repeat crackers and remaining pudding.
Top with layer of crackers.

title: dump it cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks of butter in pan.
Spread can of Thank You cherries and 1 can crushed pineapple in 11 x 14-inch cake pan. Sprinkle 1 yellow cake mix over mixture.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans and 1 cup coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: jello delight
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with sugar and butter.
Line square or oblong pan with mixture.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Dissolve each jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cool in shallow pans.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring pineapple juice to a boil. Turn down heat and add gelatin.
Boil one minute.
Then pour in large bowl and when it gets syrupy, add Cool Whip.
Stir well and fold in jello cubes.
Put this in the graham cracker crust and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: teriyaki steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over steaks to coat all sides. Marinate 3 to 4 hours.
Grill.

title: plum beautiful cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: blue cheese lover's meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crumble Blue cheese into mixing bowl. Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.

title: double fudge balls
directions: Cream together margarine, milk, salt and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in cocoa and sugar replacement.
Knead or work with hands until dough is smooth and form dough into 60 small balls. Dip balls in chocolate; cool completely.
Dip again and cool. Yield: 60 balls.

title: blackened seasoning(for fish, chicken and steaks)
directions: Mix ingredients together; store in a covered container.
Good for steaks, fish and chicken, cooked outdoors.
Fry in 1 tablespoon olive oil or butter and oil.

title: popcorn treat
directions: Mix popcorn with peanuts or pecan halves.
Place in oven on cookie sheet to keep warm 250° while you mix in a saucepan honey, salt, water, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook to a hard-crack stage.
Pour popcorn mixture into large bowl.
Slowly drizzle honey mixture over, stirring, coating evenly.
Spread onto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 250° (stirring after first 10 minutes).
Cool and break into pieces.
Make plenty Mother, because this goes fast!!!!!!

title: so simple fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients until well blended.
Keep chilled until use.

title: caesar salad
directions: Smash cloves of garlic into wood bowl, then mash and rub anchovies or use anchovy paste.
Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and oil.
Just before serving add egg and whisk dressing well.
Add romaine lettuce and top with croutons and cheese. Serve immediately.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apple slices and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
When serving, sprinkle with confectioners sugar or use whipped topping.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Combine soup, 1/4 cup milk, chicken, vegetables and pepper in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine biscuit mix, 1/3 cup milk and salt.
Drop by spoonfuls into chicken mixture.
Bake in 450° oven for 25 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil, egg and pumpkin together.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Mix well and add raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 12 to 14 minutes until lightly browned.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Bake 10 minutes at 375°, then cool.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until browned, stirring often.
Spoon off fat.

title: double chili cheese dip
directions: Smooth cream cheese in bottom of 9 in. pan.
Top with chili, green chilies, onion and olives.
Sprinkle cheese over the top. Bake uncovered 15-20 min. at 350 degrees.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar together until crumbly.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Sprinkle the rest in pie shell.
Prepare pudding with milk according to package directions.
Chill to set. Beat cream until stiff.
Spread on top of pudding mixture. Sprinkle with reserved peanut butter mixture.
Serve chilled.
You can drizzle chocolate syrup over top.

title: marinated steak italiano
directions: In shallow dish pour dressing over steak.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight. Remove steak, reserving marinade.
Grill or broil, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade, until done.
Do not brush with marinade during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: lamb stew
directions: Simmer meat in soy sauce.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover and let sizzle in its own fat until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: topsy turvy apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out half of pie crust dough on lightly floured surface to circle 1-inch larger than inverted pie plate.
Set aside.
Spread butter and up side of 9-inch pie plate. Press pecans, round side down, into butter.
Pat brown sugar over pecans.
Press dough in pie plate over brown sugar.
Place apples in large bowl; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, granulated sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and dash of salt in small bowl. Add to apples; toss.
Turn into pie crust; spread evenly to keep top level.
Roll out remaining dough on lightly floured surface to 1-inch larger than pie plate.
Place over apples, fold edge under and flute.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake 50 minutes. Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes.
Invert into serving plate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and flatten. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add a little milk, then add the egg yolks.
Put rest of milk and the butter in saucepan and heat on stove until butter is melted.
Then add heated milk mixture to the flour and sugar mixture.
Beat with a mixer.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press into ungreased pans.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Put water, sugar and coffee in a pot; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cooled, add vanilla and vodka.

title: banana chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour two 8-inch round or square pans or an oblong 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar.

Continue beating until very stiff and glossy. Sift remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, soda and salt into another bowl. Add oil, mashed bananas, half the buttermilk and flavoring. Beat 1 minute on medium speed of mixer or 150 strokes by hand. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly. Fold in nuts.
Fold in meringue.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake layers 30 to 35 minutes; oblong 40 to 45 minutes. Cool. Frost with whipped cream or fluffy white icing.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and jam. Beat. To flour, add soda, salt and spices alternately with milk to the first mixture. Beat well. Pour into greased tube cake pan. Bake at 350° about 55 minutes. Use a caramel icing.

title: great wall chicken slaw
directions: Whisk dressing ingredients in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients except noodles. Toss to mix. Cover and chill 1 hour. Just before serving, stir in noodles. Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and zucchini.
Stir well.
Add water and then flour.
Add raisins and nuts last.
Add spices and rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: mad mex nachos
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly; drain and keep warm. Place tortilla chips on a baking sheet. Combine refried beans and picante sauce in a sauce pan, heat until warm, stirring occasionally. Spoon bean mixture over chips. Top with sausage, tomatoes, cheese and peppers. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Top with guacamole and sour cream.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Arrange banana slices in bottom of pie shell.
Combine Cool Whip and vanilla; blend well.
Add sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until stiff.
Spread blueberry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: homemade granola cereal
directions: *I heat water in large plastic cup.
Add honey and oil.
Stir to mix, then pour on dry ingredients.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed using two pans.
Split each layer in half.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup of sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remaining mixture between layers.
Combine reserved mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth and spread on top and side of cake.
Store in airtight container.
Refrigerate for two days before serving to allow cake to moisten.

title: homespun meat pie
directions: Combine beef, mushrooms, egg, onion, bread crumbs and salt. Press mixture into 9-inch glass pie dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Mash potatoes, milk, cheese, parsley and salt.
Fill meat pie.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: hillbilly bean soup
directions: Wash and bring all beans to a boil.
Drain off water and add fresh water.
Add onions, celery and ham.
Add salt and pepper and cook until done.

title: chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt together.
Microwave margarine, water and cocoa just to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Mix slightly.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and soda.
Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 24 to 48.

title: claret punch
directions: In large saucepan, combine water, juice, sugar, lemon peel, allspice and cloves.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes.
Add claret.
Strain and remove lemon peel, allspice and cloves.

title: strawberry dessert(a double recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Do not add water to jello.
Serve, no need to let set.

title: sally lunn(bread)
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Cream butter and sugar together; add well beaten eggs and mix.
Add salt to flour (add a pinch of cardamom for special flavor).
Stir flour into butter-sugar mixture alternately with milk-yeast mixture (after yeast has softened in lukewarm water about 5 minutes combine with lukewarm milk before adding to flour).
Beat well with wooden spoon or power mixer.
Turn into oiled bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Beat again and pour into Bundt pan.
Let rise again; bake 45 minutes at 350°.
If top gets brown too soon, cover with aluminum foil for rest of time.

title: summer squash slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine squash, red pepper and onion. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour over squash mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate. Yield: 10 servings.

title: skillet zucchini dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain and add tomatoes, zucchini, corn, and spices.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple delight dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and place in bottom of baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients lightly and spoon over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Beat in vanilla. Bake 10 minutes at 400°, until golden brown.

title: salsa dip
directions: Stir Velveeta and salsa in saucepan on low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with chips or cut up vegetables.

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat whole eggs very lightly.
Gradually add sugar, beating steadily.
Add melted butter and soda (dissolved in small amount of milk.)
Let stand 15 minutes.
Fold in flour.
Spread flour freely on board.
Knead more flour into dough to get it stiff enough to roll with a designed rolling pin, well dusted with flour.
Cut cakes into squares by design.
Place on greased cookie sheets and let stand for 10 hours in cool place.
Preheat oven to 375°, then reduce to 300° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: lemon-blueberry trifle
directions: Cut pound cake into 1/2-inch cubes; arrange in a dessert bowl. Prepare pudding mix according to directions; pour over pound cake.
Spoon pie filling over pudding; spread whipped topping over pie filling.
Cover with plastic wrap; chill overnight.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds before serving.

title: cheese-spinach pie
directions: Place Swiss cheese on bottom of pie crust.
Sprinkle with spinach, mushrooms and Tender Chunks.
Mix next 4 ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Form crust with Oreo cookies and melted butter in 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, evaporated milk and eggs together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over this and nuts over that, then drizzle margarine on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Dump on flat surface.
Pull wax paper off while hot, then let cool.

title: easy spiced pecans
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in glass bowl or measuring cup with water and mix well.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on high for 4 minutes, stir well and microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir again and microwave 2 1/2 minutes more.
Add the pecan halves, stir well, and microwave 1 minute more.
Spread the coated pecans on waxed paper and separate with a fork.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Pour in warm water, mix.
Cook on medium to low heat until thick, stirring constantly to avoid sticking.
Let cool.
Add strawberries and mix.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Serve with cool whip on top.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together.

Mix pudding and milk in bowl and beat for 2 minutes. Add whipped topping and beat well. Add pudding mix to cream cheese mix and stir together. Alternate cookies and pudding, starting with pudding. Reserve some cookie crumbs for top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together until all the Bisquick is used up and moist. Shape into 3-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange breakfast shake
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mini pigs in a poke
directions: Roll out each biscuit until flat; cut biscuits into quarters. Roll a quarter piece around each wiener.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: ken's super pasta salad
directions: Mix all.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
This is an excellent summer salad to accompany steak or chicken.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with corn chips.

title: kona banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in mashed bananas. Sift dry ingredients together and add to banana mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into two well-greased bread loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool in pans on rack for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and continue to cool on rack.
Cover with dish towel or soft cloth while cooling.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil if you plan to freeze.

title: cracker jack popcorn
directions: Cook sugar, oleo and syrup for 5 minutes.
Add soda, vanilla and salt.
Stir and pour over popped corn and peanuts.
Bake for 1 hour in 250° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: school soup
directions: Bring to a boil. Simmer until potatoes are tender (about an hour).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together well and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9 3/4 x 9 3/4-inch casserole with pound cake cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Put flour in a measuring cup and add sugar to make 1 cup.
Mix well in a heavy saucepan.
Add eggs and mix.
Pour in pineapple.
Cook and stir until thick.
Pour over cake.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Scatter nuts on top.
Refrigerate.
(Freezes well.)

title: pecan brittle
directions: Place sugar, syrup and wax in boiler.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add nuts and cook to hard crack stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: taco scoop
directions: Amounts vary depending on the amount of plates served.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Combine cheeses and set aside.
Combine and cook ground beef, salt and onions until tender. Add pepperoni. Stir in tomato paste, water, mushrooms and oregano. Cook vermicelli; drain. Combine vermicelli and margarine. Toss well.
Add to meat sauce. Reserve 1 cup of cheese mixture.
Combine rest of cheese with meat mixture. Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole or long dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and top with pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pistachio pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let chill in refrigerator for a couple hours.
Add coconut if desired.

title: flat armenian (russia) bread with sesame seed(churek)
directions: Sprinkle the yeast and 1 teaspoon of the sugar into 1/2 cup of lukewarm (110-115F) water in a small, shallow bowl.

Let stand for 2 or 3 minutes, then stir to dissolve the yeast completely. Set the bowl aside in a warm, draft-free spot (such as an unlighted oven) for about 5 to 10 minutes, or until the mixture almost doubles in volume.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and drained tuna fish in a casserole dish.
Add cooked noodles and mix in.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes.

title: "holiday corn stuffing balls"
directions: Heat butter with water in large saucepan until butter melts. Stir in stuffing mix and add corn and parsley.
Stir in eggs.
Add more water if needed.
Shape into balls and arrange in buttered, shallow baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour. Remove from refrigerator.
Bake uncovered in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: leon's peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil, then add sugar and syrup.
Stir until dissolved and boil until it will spin a thread.
Remove from fire and add butter, soda and vanilla quickly.
Spread on two large cookie sheets that have been well buttered.
Place in cool area.

title: nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9 baking dish. Combine cake mix, 3/4 cup nuts and melted butter. Stir and press into pan. Combine cream cheese and brown sugar until well mixed. Spread over base. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup nuts. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Refrigerate when cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix together in a bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time. In a second bowl, mix dry ingredients.
In a third bowl, mix jam and sour cream together. Mix all together and put into 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the bacon.
Pour into well-greased dish.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Serves 6.

title: mother's flemish beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Dust with flour; saute in oil.
Add chopped onions and carrot; brown lightly.
Add water and seasonings.
The meat should be covered.
Simmer covered for 2 hours or until tender.
Serve with boiled potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: violet jelly
directions: Pour boiling water into quart jar packed with violet blossoms; seal.
Steep for 1 day.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Drain off all fat except 2 tablespoons.
Add onion, green pepper and okra.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in rice, broth, salt and red pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and fluff lightly.
Replace lid and let set about 15 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ron's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until tender.
In 9-inch square baking dish melt margarine.
In separate bowl combine eggs and milk and beat.
Add sugar and beat some more.
Add rice to margarine.
Add egg, milk and sugar mixture into baking dish with margarine and rice.
Stir gently, blending.
Sprinkle a bountiful amount of raisins in and stir.
Add milk to almost filling dish, allowing room for expansion while cooking.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover dish and bake in microwave until done.
Caution:
Do not overbake.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook
cups
of
sugar, white syrup and water to soft cracks stage; add margarine and nuts, mix well together before cooking again, then cook to soft crack stage (280°).
Add soda and vanilla; stir and spread rapidly on buttered cookie sheet. Cool. Break into pieces.

title: apple pudding
directions: Butter bread, both sides, and remove crusts.
Then line bottom and sides of 1 1/2-pint ovenproof dish.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
Put layer of apples sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon, then bread sprinkled with sugar, then apples all the way to the top, ending with bread.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Beat the egg in the milk until frothy and pour over the bread and fruit.
Bake in slow oven until apples are tender and bread nicely browned, about 2 hours.
Serve topped with fruit or ice cream.
Serves 4 people.
Set oven to 325°.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into measuring cup and set chunks aside. Add enough water to juice to make 3/4 cup. Add soy sauce, oil, ginger, red pepper flakes and garlic. Stir to combine. Set aside 2 tablespoons of marinade for fruit skewers and put remaining mixture into a 1-gallon zip-top plastic bag. Add tuna and seal bag. Shake well to coat fish. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into pie shell; bake 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill. Spread with whipping cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, pour into two 9 inch pie crusts. Bake for 45 minutes or until crust forms on top of pie.

title: great snickerdoodles
directions: In a large bowl at medium speed, cream butter, 1 1/2 cups of sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture until well blended.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon to mixture.
Place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: deluxe jello dessert
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Combine whipped cream, sugar, pineapple and walnuts; spread over graham crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.

title: strawberry flip
directions: Add a little strawberry juice from sweetened berries.
Mix ingredients in blender.
Serve over crushed ice.
Yield: four 6 ounce servings.

title: sandie's cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oatmeal and corn flakes. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Get an attractive glass bowl with straight sides.
Add the first 5 ingredients in layers.
Mix the sugar into mayonnaise and spread it smoothly across the top of the salad like you were frosting a cake.
Add the next 4 ingredients on top.
Cover very tightly and refrigerate overnight.
This salad may sound strange, but it's absolutely delicious.
It's very popular in the South as a buffet dish.

title: linguine carbonara
directions: Over moderate heat in a skillet, melt butter and combine with cheese.
Reduce heat and add pasta.
Toss to coat.
Add eggs and toss until eggs are cooked. Remove from heat and add crumbled bacon.
Top with parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Let butter stand at room temperature until soft.
Beat in sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add other ingredients, mixed and sifted together.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll 1/8-inch thick and cut out with cookie cutter or omit 1/4 cup flour and drop from spoon. Sprinkle with sugar or the color sprinkles.
Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a big bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add the oil, vanilla, eggs, soda and salt.
Mix and add flour.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, serving 1 1/2 cups juice.
Cut peaches in 1/2-inch cubes.
Set aside.
Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Heat 1 1/2 cups juice in saucepan.
Bring to boiling; remove from heat.
Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Stir in orange and lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Chill until it thickens.
Fold in all fruits, marshmallows, ginger, pecans, cream and mayonnaise. Spoon into 1-quart cylinder containers.
Cover and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Remove from container; cut into 1-inch slices.

title: frank davis' ol' n'awlins hogshead cheese
directions: First, drop the pigs feet and pork butt chunks into a 12-quart stock pot and add enough water to cover the meat, about 1 1/2 gallons should do it.
When the water begins to boil, a foam will form on the surface - skin it off!

When you've removed as much foam as possible, add the salt, crab boil, celery, lemon, bay leaves, onion, bell peppers, garlic, rosemary and basil and continue to cook the meats on a medium setting, skimming as necessary, until the pigs feet are tender.
This should take about 3 hours or so.
Just remember, the bottom line is you want the meats to be "super tender."

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add sauce and water, simmer 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour 1 cup sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 3 pieces uncooked noodles.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 of cheese filling.
Repeat lasagna, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagna ending with sauce. Cover with filling and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake and let cool.
Mix cheesecake filling according to directions.
Crumble 1/2 of the yellow cake and layer it in a punch bowl.
Top with 1/2 of cheesecake filling, strawberries, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, using remaining 1/2 of each of the ingredients.
If desired, garnish with coconut, pecans and cherries.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In buttered casserole, put layer of potato chips; top with tuna and cover with soup.
Repeat layers; top with chips.
Bake in 250° oven until lightly browned.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: You will need no stick cooking spray (Pam).

title: never fail cheesecake(easy !  make ahead!)
directions: Mix well with electric mixer and pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 300° oven until cake springs back.
Top with fresh, sweetened strawberries in 1 can cherry pie filling.
If I use strawberries, I put them on as served so they don't soak the cake.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients alternately with soup.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour in greased pan. Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool and frost.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. For chilled pudding, place plastic wrap on surface of hot pudding. Chill about 1 hour. Stir before serving. Sprinkle
with cinnamon and nutmeg. Serve warm.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine until it is a soft dough.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in a 450° oven.
Melt 1/2 cup butter with garlic powder.
Brush the mixture onto the biscuits.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Chill. Peel and devein shrimp.
Combine shrimp and next 6 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine Italian dressing and next 5 ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour over shrimp mixture and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: peanut and bacon sandwich
directions: Mix peanut butter and bacon well.
Spread on sandwich bread.

title: hearty tortellini-vegetable soup(yields 4 servings)
directions: In 4-quart microwavable casserole, combine mushrooms, onions, carrots, zucchini, oil and garlic and stir to coat.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) for 6 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Add remaining ingredients except tortellini and stir to combine.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Add tortellini and stir to combine; cover and microwave on Medium (50%) for 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until tortellini are soft.

title: teriyaki marinade for chicken or steaks
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate chicken or meat overnight. Excellent for grilling.

title: army gelatin salad
directions: Combine lime and orange gelatin with hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill until set.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cook cream cheese and butter at a low temperature until soft. Stir in flour.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tin.
Shape into shells.

title: chocolate custard
directions: Dissolve the cornstarch in 1/2 cup of milk.
Heat 2 1/2 cups of milk in a double boiler.
Into a saucepan, put the sugar, water and cooking chocolate.
Dissolve over boiling water, then place on heat and boil for 2 minutes.
Add to hot milk.
When the mixture has the appearance of chocolate milk instead of plain milk, the half cup of milk and cornstarch is poured in.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add the vanilla.
Pour into goblets and cool. Refrigerate.
Serve with cream.

title: ma's lentils and macaroni
directions: Check through lentils and discard any miscellaneous seeds or darkened lentils.
Rinse under cold water.
Put lentils in a pan and cover with salted water.
Cook until tender (about 15 to 20 minutes).
In a frypan, saute onions and garlic in oil until tender and slightly brown.
Add tomato paste and sugar to cooked lentils and mix well.
Add onions and garlic.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste and add water to desired consistency.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Cook rice and combine with broccoli, Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup. Top with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: berries and bits
directions: Combine condensed milk and water; add pudding and beat well. Chill 5 minutes and fold in whipped cream.
Place 2 cups mixture in a glass bowl and place a layer of vanilla wafers on top. Sprinkle with strawberries and bits.
Repeat with 1/2 pudding, wafers, strawberries and bits.
Finish with pudding.
Refrigerate. Any in season berry may be used.

title: honey cracker jacks
directions: Mix peanuts with popcorn. Heat honey and butter in a saucepan, until well blended. Cool. Pour over popcorn and peanuts and stir well. When well coated, spread on a cookie sheet in a single layer. Bake at 350° for 5-10 min. Turn several times, being careful not to overcook.

title: four bean enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas tightly in foil.
Heat at 350° for 10 minutes or until warm.
Combine beans and cheese soup.
Place 1/3 cup on each tortilla.
Roll and place (seam side down) in a baking dish.
Stir together enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Pour over enchiladas. Cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Top with olives and green pepper.

title: great chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in a bowl; mix well with electric mixer at medium-high speed.
Pour into greased and floured pans; bake.
Top with your favorite chocolate or white frosting.
For cupcakes bake 15 minutes, for layers bake 30 minutes and 9 x 13-inch pan bake 40 minutes.

title: health muffins
directions: Add boiling water to soda, then add oil and any spices.
Cool to lukewarm.
Now add sugar and eggs; mix well. Set aside. Combine flour, cereals, wheat germ, raisins and nuts in a huge bowl.
Pour in lukewarm mixture, then add buttermilk.
Stir only enough to moisten. Batter will keep in sealed container for up to 6 weeks in refrigerator or bake muffins and freeze.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Fill muffin tins to 2/3 full only.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt shortening; add flour and brown.
Add water, enchilada sauce and tomato sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Boil chicken until done; cool and debone.
Add chilies, olives and onions.
Mix well with hands.
Put aside.
Heat oil; dip each tortilla quickly to soften.
Set aside.
Put filling in, roll up, add sauce and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious orange salad
directions: Shake jello
over
fruit and mix.
Fold in Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: perogies
directions: Mix into a dough.
Roll out thin and cut into rounds.
Fill with mashed potato and grated cheese.
Fold over and seal edges. Freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to eggs mixed well with oil.
Blend in carrots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix frosting ingredients until smooth. Spread over cooled cake.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, cornstarch, butter and eggs.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until well blended and uniform.
Add the buttermilk and mix well.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until set and brown on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ice cream in a blender
directions: In a blender, sprinkle gelatin over cold milk and let stand 4 minutes.
Add hot milk and process in blender 2 minutes. Gradually add fruit, sugar and vanilla.
Process until smooth.
Pour into bowl and chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Fold chilled gelatin mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into an 8-inch baking pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: aunt belle's chicken noodles(heritage)
directions: In a bowl, beat egg and add enough sifted flour with salt to make a stiff dough.
Place on lightly floured board and roll very thin.
Flour top of pastry and roll into long roll.
Cut in rounds.
To one quart of seasoned chicken broth, heated to a boil, drop the rolled noodles and cook for one hour.
Serve with chicken which has been removed from bone and placed on platter.

title: spicy peanut butter chinese chicken
directions: In medium bowl stir together chicken, cucumber, scallion, ginger and garlic; mix well.
In small bowl stir together peanut butter, water, soy sauce, vinegar, oil, sugar and hot pepper sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken and toss gently.
Serve on watercress and garnish with chopped peanuts if desired.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from bones.
Save broth.
Saute onion and celery in melted butter.
Add to crumb mixture.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in shallow pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican pickles
directions: Any vegetable that will pickle and stay firm such as carrots, cauliflower, cucumber, celery, green tomatoes, small onion, peppers (sweet or hot) or green beans.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chips and 14 ounces of almond bark in a bowl in microwave oven, approximately 2 minutes, until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir together.
Pour onto a greased pizza pan.
Place cherries cut in half on top.
Sprinkle coconut over cherries.
Melt remaining 2 ounces of almond bark with oil in microwave approximately 1 minute.
String over top of pizza. Refrigerate.

title: coconut cake
directions: Thaw coconut and Cool Whip. Make cake according to directions. Bake in 9 x 13 pan. While cake is still hot, punch holes in it and pour cream of coconut on top. Mix 1 package of coconut and Cool Whip. Frost cool cake. Sprinkle the other package of coconut on top. Refrigerate.

title: leesey's pickles
directions: Start with a gallon of kosher dill pickles.
Drain juice. Slice pickles as you wish (I prefer crosswise, approximately 1/4-inch pieces).
Pack the gallon jars with layers of sugar, spice bag and pickle slices, making four layers, alternating a layer of sugar in the bottom of the jar, then a spice bag, pickles, etc.

title: new york state beef casserole
directions: Place in layers in casserole baking dish.
Make three layers and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie 3
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and flour.
Add eggs and beat well. Then add remainder of ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: iced coffee
directions: Place in an electric blender the coffee, milk, sugar, vanilla and ice cubes (half of the amount at a time) until light and frothy.
Pour into cups and top with whipped cream and a dash of nutmeg.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in casserole dish or pan.
Mix fruit and 3/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Make batter by combining last 3 ingredients.
Pour batter into butter in dish.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Batter will rise to the top.

title: hal's hot fudge sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt oleo and add other ingredients. Bring to full boil and cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat and place in sink of cold water to cool while beating. Cool and serve over ice cream, brownies, etc.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except carrots and pecans).
Beat until smooth.
Fold by hand in carrots and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured round cake pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: kellogg ladies of elks pie crust for our pasties
directions: Put egg in cup and mix with fork; add oil to measure 1/2 cup. Fill to full cup with water.
Add shortening and salt; mix.
Will make 3 to 4 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: fairy drop cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and margarine.
Blend in oil and margarine to fluffy mixture.
Add eggs and flavoring and beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add; blend well.
Chill several hours.
Roll in small balls, then roll in sugar.
Flatten slightly with small glass.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes a large batch of very delicious cookies.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour in pan or dish. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Ovens vary.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef, ground pork, onion and garlic in a large saucepan until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off all fat. Add tomatoes.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar and salt.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and oregano.

title: one dish pork chop casserole
directions: In a deep dish (casserole or baking), chop up onion; add green beans, carrots and sliced up potatoes.
Stir.
Add 1/4 cup milk and 1/2 can soup to the mixture.
Place pork chops on top of mixture; add rest of soup on top of each pork chop.
Put in oven for an hour at least until pork chops turn brown and are done (350°).

title: slender soup(46 calories per cup)
directions: Melt margarine in a soup pot.
Add onions; cook, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini; cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in spinach and basil.
Let rest for five minutes.
Cool.
Puree in a blender.
Return to soup pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until heated through.
Before serving, stir in fresh lemon juice.

title: shrimp kabobs
directions: Peel shrimp and devein; set aside.
Combine lemon juice and the next 7 ingredients in a dish; set aside.
Arrange shrimp on 6-inch bamboo skewers that have been soaked in water.
Place in lemon juice mixture, turning to coat.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours. Place shrimp on rack sprayed with cooking spray into broiler pan. Broil 6 inches from heat with oven door partly open 3 to 4 minutes on each side, basting with the marinade.
Serve hot or cold.

title: like ice cream pie
directions: Smoothly blend first 3 ingredients.
Add the Bits 'O Brickle; fold in topping.
Pile into crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix in mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until firm in pan.
Makes 3 layers.

title: pecan pineapple dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese and lime jello with mixer.
Add water and mix well.
Let set for 5 minutes. Add pineapple and nuts.
Put in mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: cream puffs with fruit sauce
directions: Puffs:
Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once; stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and add eggs all at once.
Stir vigorously until smooth (may take up to 5 minutes of stirring).

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit like grapes, strawberries, pineapple chunks and plenty of toothpicks for dipping.

title: carrot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 c. lukewarm water.
Combine with the 1 c. of warm water and beaten egg.
Add the remaining ingredients and knead well.
Put in a warm place and let stand about 1 hour. Work down and let rise again until light or double in bulk.
Makes a rather soft dough; you may have to add more flour.
Pinch off small portions of dough and form into balls.
Arrange 3 balls in each greased muffin cup.
Brush with butter and let rise.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spiced tea punch
directions: Boil 1 quart water with cloves, cinnamon and allspice for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sugar, stirring well.
Add tea bags, cover and allow to cool, about 2 hours.
Add remaining 2 qts. water, orange juice and lemonade.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated in a covered container.
Will keep about 5 days.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix together everything except the crab meat to soften.
Then add the crab meat.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: oven peanut bars
directions: Mix flour, butter, brown sugar and salt until crumbly.
Pat flat into pans.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.
Melt chips, butter, water and syrup and pour into peanuts.
Spread over hot crumb base and return to oven 10 minutes.
Loosen edges while warm.
Cool and cut into desired sizes.
Makes 48 (2-inch) squares.

title: peach and poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins for a dozen muffins.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add tomatoes, catsup, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and simmer.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; heat 1 cup water and 1/2 cup salt until salt dissolves. Add remaining water and cool. Pour saltwater over cucumbers. Add onion and chill for 3 hours. Drain and rinse cucumbers in cold water.

title: my breakfast bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown sausage and drain.
Grease 9-inch round pie plate.
Spread crumbled sausage in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix bisquick, milk, and eggs until blended.
Pour over sausage.
Bake about 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
About 6 servings.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all together. Put in casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
With a small spoon, scoop out zucchini centers, making 1/4-inch thick shells.
Finely chop zucchini centers.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, combine chopped zucchini with 1 tablespoon butter and onions.
Stir often until zucchini is lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Stir together zucchini mixture, rice, cheese and egg.
Mound filling equally into zucchini shells in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover tightly with foil; bake in a 400° oven until zucchini shells are tender when pierced, about 20 minutes.

title: come on over cake
directions: Beat egg whites, set aside.
Mix crushed cracker crumbs with remaining crust ingredients.
Fold in egg whites last. Spread in a 9x13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Allow to cool.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat; add salt, garlic and 1/2 pound cheese and onion, simmer 10 minutes.
Heat soup, milk, green onions, chilies, pimentos and grated cheese together in saucepan. Softened tortillas in hot oil and drain.
Fill each tortilla with meat mixture.
Roll tightly and place in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour soup and cheese mixture over all and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: california marinade sauce
directions: Mix well.
Place meat in sauce for 45 minutes before cooking.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream the butter and vanilla until smooth. Blend in sugar, flour and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll in confectioners sugar. Double if you want.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine
sugar,
salt,	Karo
and
water in 8-cup glass measuring
cup.
Microwave	on High, uncovered, for 3 minutes. Stir; microwave
on
High,	uncovered,
for 8 to 10 minutes or until small
amount
dropped
in
very cold water forms a hard ball (about 260° on candy thermometer).

title: bob wade's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt oleo; add vinegar, lemon, chopped fine garlic, salt and pepper to taste; simmer.
Add all other ingredients; continue to simmer.
If oleo comes to top, add 1/4 cup beer to emulsify while stirring.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix lemon and lime Jell-O with water; let cool.
Add cream cheese and whip with mixer until well blended.
Add Miracle Whip, Pet milk, crushed pineapple, pecans and cucumber juice or pieces. Chill.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: garlic beef
directions: Cut beef fillet into strips about 1 1/2 x 1/4-inches.
(Best to freeze fillet and slice when semi-frozen.)
Crush garlic and mix with sugar, soy sauce, stock and sherry.
Add the meat; stir and toss well into mixture.
Leave for about 30 minutes (stir occasionally).
Heat oil in wok or frypan and fry beef over high heat for 3 minutes, stirring all the time.
Serve immediately over rice or noodles.
Serves 2.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie(opal's)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix all together and pour into deep dish pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes in hot oven.
Turn to 250° and bake until golden brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flavors.
Make paste of cocoa and food color.
Add to first mixture.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl; add to batter and blend.
Bake in 3 (9 or 10-inch) pans for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.
Cover with frosting of your choice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, flour, milk, yolks of eggs and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and let cool.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue that has been beaten until stiff peaks form.
Add 5 tbsp. sugar to meringue and 1/4 tsp. cream of tartar.
Brown at 350 degrees.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Bake for six minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies, but recipe can be halved.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli with other ingredients, spread in greased casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marinade for chuck roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and put chuck roast in the bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, put chuck roast on and grill to desired doneness and serve sliced thinly.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all other ingredients, except flour, with yeast and water.
Cottage cheese should be at room temperature.
Soak a few minutes.
Add flour; mix with spoon. Cover.
Let rise in warm place for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir down and put in well-greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Brush while warm with 1 tablespoon butter and salt the top. Remove from dish, cut and serve warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in bananas and nuts, then flour, baking soda and salt.
Spread in greased loaf pan.
Bake for 55 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour and soda; add to creamed mixture along with buttermilk and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites, nuts and coconut.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) pans or 2 square pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and spread the first 3 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, milk and Cool Whip until creamy.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Spread on the crust and chill.
Use any kind of fruit topping.

title: steamed apple pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Work in butter with tips of fingers and add milk.
Line bottom and sides of a well-greased mold with sugar, salt and nutmeg, mixed.
Steam 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve with a cream sauce.

title: arthur's salsa
directions: Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Layer in bottom of dish.
Pour cream of potato soup over top of ground beef, then add a layer of grated cheese, then top layer with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until Tots are done.

title: chicken cacciatore(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart microproof casserole, combine onion, green pepper and margarine.
Cook covered on High (maximum power) 4 to 5 minutes or until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes and flour. Stir until smooth.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except chicken.
Cook covered on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes.
Add chicken pieces, immersing them in sauce.
Cook covered on High 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir once during cooking.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving on cooked spaghetti or rice.

title: easy rice soup
directions: Brown meat in medium saucepan.
Pour off as much fat as possible.
Add water, bouillon, stewed tomatoes, vegetables and onion and garlic powders.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in rice; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: adobo
directions: Dice cloves of garlic and put into deep saucepan with 1 cap full of oil to fry it up.
Add your vinegar, soy sauce and chicken. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, then let simmer for 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: mustard pickles (cold)
directions: Wash pickles and pack in jars.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over on pickles in jars and seal at once.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in pan.
Stir constantly and bring to a hard boil for 3 minutes.
Take off the stove and add baking soda and cream of tartar.

title: sloppy joe cups
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper; salt and pepper. Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and brown sugar.
Grease 1 (8 part) muffin pan.
Spread buttermilk biscuits out flat and place in muffin pan (like a little pie crust).
Place 3 tablespoons meat mixture in cups.
Place cheese on top.
Bake until lite brown at 350°, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and 1/2 package of taco seasoning. In a large bowl, tear lettuce into small pieces.
Add tomatoes, grated cheese and drained kidney beans.
Add hamburger mixture. At the last minute, add the Doritos (crushed) and French dressing.

title: delicious pound cake
directions: Set eggs, margarine, shortening and milk out to reach room temperature.
Cream margarine and shortening well.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done when tested with a straw.

title: cream of pumpkin soup
directions: Heat pumpkin, chicken stock, potato and onion in large saucepan over medium heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 25 minutes.
Strain off liquid and add vegetables to food processor using chopping blade to make smooth puree.
Return puree to liquid in saucepan.
(Soup may be prepared up to this point in advance, refrigerated.)
Just before serving, heat soup to simmering.
Add salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Remove from heat and stir in cream.

title: apple cinnamon nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with low-fat spray.
Mix egg substitute, sugar and applesauce; add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture alternating with apples.
Add pecans.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
For easier slicing and extra moist, rich bread, wrap warm loaf tightly after removing from pan.
Store overnight for best flavor and easier slicing.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pudding mix and spice in bowl.
Mix on low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups whipped topping. Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Top with remaining whipped topping.

title: pumpkin banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin and bananas.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix just until moistened. Stir in nuts.
Spread into 2 greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool upright in pans for 5 minutes; remove from pans.

title: orange spice pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides in bowl.
Combine all other ingredients except flour and water.
Pour over roast.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove meat to platter (discard bay leaf).
Mix flour and water and add to juice to make gravy.

title: fruit with strawberry yogurt
directions: Arrange fruit, except strawberries, on a serving platter. Combine yogurt and strawberries.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Place on platter with fruit.
To serve, dip fruit in yogurt or spoon yogurt over each serving.
Serves 8.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Then stir in meal. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: linda's chile verde
directions: Add vegetable mixture to pork with 3 cups chicken broth, 2 cups water, 2 teaspoons cumin and 2 teaspoons oregano.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours until meat is very tender. Thicken with cornstarch and water if necessary.

title: mary's meatloaf casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with cooking spray.
Place ground chuck in dish; make well in middle of meat.
Add all other ingredients except potatoes and carrots.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Arrange in a lengthwise loaf in middle of dish.
Spread approximately 1 1/2 Tbsp. ketchup on top of loaf; sprinkle with ground black pepper. Sprinkle bottom of dish on both sides of meat loaf with additional salt and pepper.

title: turkey or chicken crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine or butter until smooth.
Add turkey, salt, pepper, milk and chives.
Mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press rolls to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each square.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center.
Twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush top with reserved butter.
Dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: spritz
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add 3 egg yolks and vanilla, mixing well. Stir in flour until well blended. Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake preheated oven 400° for 8 minutes. Don't overbake. Watch carefully.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients.
Add the blueberries.
Then add the beaten egg, milk and melted shortening, mixed together. Stir only enough to mix.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts.
Stir enough to mix well.
Don't beat.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix sugar, melted butter and lemon extract; beat in eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Beat just enough to blend.
Fold in rind and nuts.
Bake 1 hour or more at 350° in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with waxed paper on bottom. Let cool slightly.
Remove from pan and place on foil.

title: lemon-pepper potatoes
directions: In an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan, combine the package of Butter Buds chives and lemon-pepper seasoning.
Stir in water.
Add the potatoes, toss to coat well.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and beginning to brown, stirring at least twice.
Serves 6.

title: ham and cheese flips
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Separate biscuits and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each biscuit into a 5 inch circle.
Spoon about 1/2 c. ham mixture onto half of each biscuit.
Brush edges with water; fold dough over filling pressing edges with a fork to seal.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix soup, tomatoes and milk.
Brown hamburger and onion together.
Layer Doritos in casserole dish.
Sprinkle hamburger over Doritos.
Pour soup mixture over hamburger.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cream
egg yolks and sugar in a boiler.
Cook until it comes
to a full boil.
Instantly add the mixture of flour, cornstarch and
sugar
which
you
mixed
in a small bowl with water.
Pick
a bowl large enough to layer a layer of cookies, layer
of bananas and layer of bread.
After the first mixture has thickened,
pour over your layers in the bowl.
After the pudding cools, add the kind of topping you like.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Mix up good and drop by teaspoons far apart.
Cook in 300° preheated oven.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook pasta per directions; cool.
Finely chop the crab, celery and onion.
Combine with cooled pasta and add dressing.
Serve chilled.

title: butterballs
directions: Mix together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll balls of 1 teaspoon of dough.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar again.

title: don't last cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir in pineapple.
Slowly add flour.
Beat well.
Fold in bananas.
Bake in heavy tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine and beat until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured cake pan.
This is an easy cake for children to learn baking with.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter; cube.
Place cubes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with crumbled sausage.
Top with shredded cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour mixture over cheese.
Chill at least 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (until brown).

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat thoroughly.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to tuna mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds. Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt. Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix apples, walnuts and coconut.
Add to other ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If too dry, add another egg.
Make into balls.
Brown in frying pan with 1/2 inch oil in pan.
Put meat balls into sauce when it is about 1 hour from being done. Additional drippings may be added from the meat ball oil.

title: easy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo in pan and boil for 30 seconds.
Add vanilla and chips.
Stir until easy to spread.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1 cup pudding into 3-quart bowl.
Top with vanilla wafers, then strawberries. Repeat layers.
Chill thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hungarian dumplings
directions: Combine flour, eggs and salt.
Add water.
Beat well until dough is gummy.
Drop by spoonful into boiling salted water.
Boil 2 additional minutes.
Drain, rinse with hot water.
Fry 2 tablespoons butter until brown.
Pour over dumplings.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: m&m holiday cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in 3/4 cup M&M's.

title: potato refrigerator roll dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour hot water over potato flakes; let stand 3 minutes. Stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Add yeast, eggs and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour until dough comes away from bowl.
Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes (dough will spring back when pressed firmly with finger).
Place in a large, buttered bowl; brush top of dough with soft butter.
Cover with damp cloth and store in refrigerator (will keep about 5 days).
When ready to use, punch down dough and cut off amount needed for desired shapes.
For each in handling, use only 1/3 of the dough at a time.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine ingredients in the order listed.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours over pan of water.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and combine with remaining ingredients. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wedding potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside 1 cup cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: orange-pineapple delight
directions: Whip the first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Let mixture set slightly in refrigerator.
Add Dream Whip and pecan pieces.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into a quart size, buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: boneless chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 5-quart pot.
While rice is cooking, brown chicken, sausages and mushrooms in vegetable oil.
Add 1/4 cup water and oyster sauce.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste. When water in rice is almost completely evaporated, punch holes in rice with chop sticks.
Pour all ingredients on top of rice, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add green onions, stir and serve. Serves four to six.

title: zucchini and rice bake
directions: Coarsely grate zucchini into sieve set over bowl.
Squeeze and press squash down to extract liquid, which will collect in bowl. Simmer onion in 1/4 cup oil for about 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and garlic; toss a minute or two.
Stir in flour; cook another couple of minutes.
Measure zucchini juices.
Add enough milk to equal 1 1/2 cups.
Blend into squash mixture.
Add rice, thyme, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup Parmesan.
Pour into a buttered rectangular baking dish; sprinkle remaining 2 tablespoons each cheese and oil over top.
Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes, or until brown and bubbly and all liquid is absorbed.

title: roasted fall vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Place the beets and turnip in a 9 x 9 inch baking dish. Cut an X in the root end of the onions and place them in the dish. Drizzle the olive oil over the vegetables and add the rosemary and salt. Stir to coat the vegetables with oil. Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour, or until the vegetables are golden brown and tender. Serve hot.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Cook beans until tender (3 to 4 hours) or in crock-pot.
(If in crock-pot, start them in the morning and they will be ready when you return home from work.)
When the beans are tender, drain.

title: harvest pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together pumpkin, egg whites, Egg Beaters and applesauce. Stir in remaining ingredients except powdered sugar and juice. Pour into loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice and pour over warm bread while in the pan.
Let cool slightly and remove from pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: crab sandwich
directions: Stir together and spread on English muffins.
Bake at 450° until bubbly.
Makes 12 halves.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream sugar in Crisco.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flavor and mix well.
Add baking powder to flour; mix well.
Knead and roll into ropes; cut into 2 1/2-inch lengths.
Dip pieces into milk and roll on sesame seeds.
Place in greased baking pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: mushroom wild rice chowder
directions: In a soup pot, heat oil. Add mushrooms and celery and saute 2 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables and cook over medium-low heat, stirring for 1 minute.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly; cook over medium heat until mixture is somewhat thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly. Garnish with paprika and toasted almonds, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rheumatism tea
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Cool and sip until you feel better.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in oil.
Add meat.
Cook until red color disappears.
Add remaining ingredients, except nachos and cheese.
Cover.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Layer into greased casserole:
meat, nachos, cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mommy's dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Mix rest of ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon onto pieces of chicken.
Steam 12 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef in large kettle until it loses its red color.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and chopped onion.
Add tomato juice, water and chili seasoning; stir until dissolved.
Cook slowly, about 30 minutes, then simmer about an hour or two.
Add beans just before serving.
Do not cook with chili.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter over low heat; blend in sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add powdered sugar to make a spreading consistency.
Beat well and frost cake.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown beef and onion. Stir in tomato paste and seasonings. Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Place biscuits in muffin tins, greased over bottom and up sides.
Spoon in 1/4 cup meat mixture. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate covered mints
directions: Mix together and form flat patties.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Melt chocolate with wax.
Using fork, dip patties in chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.
Allow chocolate to set at room temperature.
Makes 5 dozen mints.

title: barbecue sauce(for chicken or chopped pork)
directions: Mix well.
Cook
and
stir
on	medium heat to boiling. Simmer and stir
often for 10 minutes. This sauce is great for oven barbecue meat.
