Keep in refrigerator.

title: easy cinnamon-raisin biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Mix 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Add onion, pepper, cheese, garlic powder and Doritos.
Mix well.
Place in at least a 3 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix Ro-Tel, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup together.
Pour over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over fruity side of cake.

title: coconut pie or tarts
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Stir in all ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch deep dish pie crust or 16 tarts.
Bake pie at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Bake tart at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: rhubarb puff
directions: Mix rhubarb with sugar; put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Add milk. Pour over rhubarb.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, salt and two eggs.
Mix well. Pour into greased medium-sized baking dish.
Mix Parmesan cheese and one egg.
Pour over top. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour or until top is browned.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add tomato sauce.
Serve as a side sauce.

title: filled cookie dough
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat. Add cream and rest of the ingredients.
Makes a smooth dough. Roll out thin and cut a round disc.
Put on a teaspoon of any kind of filling (cherry, apple, blueberry, etc.).
Place another disc on top and crimp edges with a fork.
(Can also use just one disc and fold over.)
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Bake in 9-inch pie plate at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until set.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Stir in flour and butter and mix well.
Turn into buttered
8 x
8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and add garlic powder to taste.
Roll in a ball in chopped nuts.

title: ky - punch
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients together in punch bowl. Add sugar to taste. Add ice.

title: hot dog octopus
directions: Cut hot dogs in half.
Cut in half 3/4 way up hot dog.
Cut four times.
Place into pan with 1/4 full of boiling water, with strips down.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Legs will curl up like an octopus.
Kids love it!

title: corn dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with vegetable crackers or any chips.

title: bimini key lime pie
directions: Place milk, cream cheese and lime juice in bowl.
Whip with electric mixer until smooth.
Add vanilla. Mix until smooth.
Pour mix into crust.
Chill in refrigerator until set, about 3 to 4 hours. Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: *Can use 1 stick of butter and 1 stick of margarine.

title: buffalo chicken wings(a la chocowinity)
directions: Melt the butter and add the pepper and bottle of Texas Pete. Pour over the chicken wings in a container with a lid.
Cover. Marinate for several hours, turning and shaking during the time period.
Grill the wings and baste with marinade sauce until done.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: With blender, mix strawberries, lemonade and sugar. With blender running, add ice cubes one at a time. Mixture will be slushly. Servers 4.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix and undrained pineapple.
Fold in marshmallows, nuts and whipped topping.
Refrigerate overnight or until well chilled.

title: rice casserole #3
directions: Melt
margarine;
stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole
dish
in a 350° oven for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: champagne pick-me-up
directions: Combine the orange and lemon juices, grenadine, brandy and ice cubes in a mixing glass.
Place shaker on top of the mixing glass and shake vigorously.
Remove shaker.
Place a strainer on top of the mixing glass; pour into a large wine glass.
Rinse shaker with the champagne and pour it slowly into the wine glass.
Makes 1 drink.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Add coconut.
Add Cool Whip last. Ice cake and keep refrigerated.
Can be frozen.

title: florida dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in grapefruit juice and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add salad oil, Tabasco and catsup.
Makes 1 cup.

title: christmas punch
directions: May be made ahead and frozen.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 75.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers(makes 12 to 18 peppers)
directions: Cook ground meat and sausage.
Drain.
Add onions and cook until done.
Drain.
Add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted. Stuff peppers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add corn syrup (I prefer white syrup instead of the dark).
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour into a 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve red raspberry jello according to the directions. Jell in a 9x13 pan. Dissolve plain gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Heat one cup of half and half with 1 cup sugar. Bring to a boil. Mix in gelatin. Add 1 tsp. vanilla and cream cheese. Beat until smooth. Cool. Pour over first layer. Sprinkle pecans on top and jell.

title: candied apples
directions: You will need skewers.

title: mom's turkey dressing
directions: Fry ground pork with onion; cool.
Cube bread and allow time for it to dry slightly (overnight).
Add sage and eggs to bread, then pork with onion.
Add water to get desired consistency.
(Best to prepare and refrigerate one night prior to stuffing turkey.)

title: zucchini macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in a large saucepan of boiling, salted water until tender, but still firm (7 to 10 minutes).
Stir in shredded zucchini during last minute.
Scoop out and reserve 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Drain macaroni and zucchini.
Place in 1 1/2-quart microwavable serving casserole.
Add the reserved liquid and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, then stir.
Sprinkle with additional paprika.
Cook 1 more minute. Or can bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Serves 4.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems from mushrooms; drain.
Mix together soup and sausage.
Stuff mushrooms with sausage and soup mixture. Sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a shallow pan.
Add a small amount of water to pan when baking.

title: fudge cake or brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa and eggs. Add pecans. Oven at 400°, bake 20 minutes.
Turn off oven in 15 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in water according to package directions. Drain and set aside. Saut onion and jalapeo peppers in butter, adding cheese and mushroom soup. Add cooked rice and broccoli after cheese is completely melted. Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add pizza sauce and oregano; heat.
When heated, add sharp Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour fondue dip into fondue pot.
Dip with pieces of Italian bread.

title: easy southwest dip
directions: In a medium bowl, stir sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, salsa, chili powder and cilantro until well mixed. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or cut up vegetables.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: anytime casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly; drain well.
Add seasoning mix, water, tomato paste and corn.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to directions; rinse well with cold water.
Combine macaroni and meat mixture.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: balsamic dressing
directions: Whisk together all ingredients except oil. Add oil slowly while stirring other ingredients.

title: oatmeal nut bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, salt, and undissolved yeast.
Heat water, milk, molasses and margarine over low heat until liquids are 120° to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients, beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occassionally.
Add eggs, cooked oatmeal and 1 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes . Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto floured board, knead 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover; let rise, until doubled about 1 hour.
Punch down; knead in pecans.
Divide dough into 3 equal pieces.
Shape into loaves.
Place in 3 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until done.
Remove and cool on wire racks.
See other recipe for bread machine adaptation.

title: baked pears
directions: Remove the core of each pear from the bottom.
Bring juices and 1 cup water to a rolling boil.
Add fresh cranberries and return to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Mix 1/4 cup cold water with cornstarch until smooth.
Add to cranberry mixture and stir until sauce thickens.
Arrange pears in a tray and cover with the sauce.
Bake, covered, at 400° until tender, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Cube cooked and boned chicken.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, milk, green chilies and chopped onion.
Place corn chips in bottom of greased shallow casserole dish.
Next place half of the chicken.
Cover it with half of the soup mixture.
Repeat three layers again.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: almond icing
directions: Beat cream, sugar, butter and egg together until well creamed. Boil gently for 10 to 15 minutes in double boiler; do not let it burn.
Remove from oven and stir in almonds.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add almond extract when cool.
Spread icing on cold cake.
Cover almond icing with white butter icing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cranberries, port wine or cranberry juice and crushed pineapple.
Chill.

title: meat pie roma
directions: Brown meat and peppers.
Add spaghetti mix, tomato paste and water.
Cook for 10 minutes on low.
Place biscuits in greased Pyrex dish, and mash flat.
Then add layer of meat sauce, layer of cheese and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: linguine and broccoli
directions: Boil linguine for 10 minutes. Stir and boil 2 more minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Freeze.
(I freeze on cookie sheet, then place in bags in freezer.)
While still frozen, place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or longer.
Makes 60 to 70.

title: italian green beans
directions: Cook green beans in salted water until tender.
Drain the water and pour the melted butter over the beans.
Sprinkle pepper in the beans and mix well.
Add the grated cheese on the beans.

title: ron's favorite oatmeal cake
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in covered bowl; let stand 20 minutes. Combine all ingredients until all is wet.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Baker's Joy.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with German chocolate icing.

title: cherry dip
directions: Chop cherries.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix well, adding cherry juice until smooth.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: broccoli chicken pasta casserole(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat Crisco oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir just until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, ketchup, basil, oregano and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: stuffed spaghetti squash
directions: Cook squash whole in microwave until fork enters squash easily or cut squash in half (long length) and remove seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in pan of 1/2-inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Saute the onion, garlic and celery in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, rice, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Stuff the cooked squash and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: easy lemon cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft, blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat until well mixed, about 1 minute.
Pour at once into crust.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill.

title: fancy baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick potatoes with fork.
Bake for 1 hour in oven.
When cooked, remove from oven.
Cutting lengthwise, slice off thin top from each potato.
Spoon out flesh, leaving enough to support shell.
Set 4 shells aside.
Force flesh through fine sieve into bowl.
Add butter, egg and nutmeg; season well. Incorporate whipped cream and stuff potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 5 minutes.

title: italiano rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini.
Combine with next 5 ingredients.
Blend olive oil, vinegar, seasoning, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Toss dressing with salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese treats
directions: Beat cream cheese on medium speed until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in miniature baking cups.
Spoon in mixture to approximately 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Chill overnight.
Add fruit topping.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and raw sausage; add Bisquick gradually.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Roll into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Heat fruit.
Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, beating until smooth. Pour this into butter in casserole.
Do not stir.
Pour hot fruit in the middle of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Spray Pam on casserole dish. Layer hamburger, green beans and juice, sliced potatoes and sliced onion. Then rest of hamburger on top. Pour over tomato soup. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in heavy ovenproof skillet. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into hot skillet. Bake 15 minutes. Prick bottom of pancake with fork. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: quickie pie
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine flour, milk and sugar. Pour into dish with melted butter. Pour fruit on top of batter (do not stir). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly gingerbread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Combine water and molasses.
Add to creamed mixture, then add flour mixture.
Turn into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle 1 heaping cup shelled pecans over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar; blend well.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Stir in mincemeat and flour.
Drop by spoon on greased baking sheet 2 inches apart. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: corn bake
directions: Combine cream-style corn, drained whole kernel corn and next six ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: uncle bob's hot dog chili
directions: Mix ground beef with tomato juice; add onion and bay leaf. Bring to boil and cook until tomato juice is cooked off.
Add balance of ingredients; simmer 1 hour.
Drain off fat with a spoon.
Add catsup and water to thin a little.
May need more chili powder to your taste.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in flour and brown in small amount of oil. Place in oven-safe dish.
Mix soup, milk, water and onion.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve over rice or toast.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat the eggs with a whip.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chopped broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add rice and salt to boiling water.
Cook until water is absorbed.
Fix broccoli according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients (except cheese) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese on top and bake at 325° for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: caramel dip
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.
Dip apple slices in mixture.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Press in a loaf pan and let set in refrigerator.
Very rich.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly; reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg until well mixed.
Press into prepared pan. Pour cherry pie filling over crust.
Spread to cover.
To reserved crumbs, in large bowl, add remaining 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly and spread over cherry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo.
Add egg.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix alternately with 1 cup milk.
Add blueberries.
Bake as cake or muffins in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Put fish fillet in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour soup over fish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Add a few onion slices and paprika.
Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine soup, cheese, mushrooms, chicken, onion, salt and pepper.
Separate crescent roll dough.
Press long edges of 2 triangles together to make a rectangle (make 8).
Pat or roll to flatten.
Place about 1/2 cup of mixture in center.
Wrap dough around, pressing edges to seal.
Dip rolls in egg; coat with cornflake crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, onion, salt, flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Stir in potatoes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drop batter onto hot skillet.
Use 1/2 cup mixture per pancake.
Fry until golden brown.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square baking pan with no-stick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings. Prep time:
15 minutes.

title: breezy, cheesy chicken
directions: In a large baking pan or dish (non-stick is best), place chicken and top with cheese.
Mix together soup and water.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: nutty pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fluffy dilled carrots and potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, bring 2 inches of water to boiling.
Add carrots and potatoes or parsnip.
Return to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until very tender; drain.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: In large bowl, combine and thoroughly blend eggs, sugar, spices and salt.
Stir in sour cream and raisins.
Pour into the unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: calico salad
directions: Cook macaroni and salt to taste.
Rinse and drain all beans and pimento.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: veggy bars
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on a 13 x 18 cookie sheet. Bake at 350 for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown. Set aside to cool. Mix ranch dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream together. Spread on top of cooled crust. Then spread with the mixture of finely chopped vegetables. Set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Cut in squares.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy. Add mayonnaise.
Drain juice from crushed pineapple, cherries and fruit cocktail.
Add to mixture.
Add marshmallows and fold in Cool Whip.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Sift the flour and salt into bowl.
Blend the Crisco into flour.
Add the cold water, enough to hold mixture together.

title: orange-cranberry sauce
directions: Drain oranges, reserving 1/4 cup of syrup.
In 2-quart saucepan, cook cranberries, sugar, ginger and reserved syrup. Cook covered on high 7 to 11 minutes or until cranberries pop. Stir twice during cooking.
Stir in oranges and nuts; chill. Makes 3 cups.

title: wassail
directions: Put juices and sugar in 24-cup percolator.
Put other ingredients in basket.
Perk.
Serve hot.
Great at Christmas for a crowd.

title: plum cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together.
Mix oil and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour mixture by tablespoons, mixing well.
Add plums.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack for about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Sift with confectioners sugar while warm.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Simmer squash in boiling salted water until tender for about 20 minutes.
Slice in half lengthwise and scoop out insides, leaving shells intact.
Drain and mash squash meat with remaining ingredients and stuff into squash shells.
Sprinkle with additional cheese; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Takes time, but worth the effort!)

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Drain liquid from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil and dissolve gelatin in it.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half into mold or baking dish and let set up in refrigerator.
Spread with sour cream.
Top with additional gelatin mixture and return to refrigerator to set.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Melt wax and chocolate chips together.
Melt butter and mix sugar
and peanut butter.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls, then dip into the chocolate.

title: hot dog meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf in a shallow pan for a dry loaf or place in a loaf pan for a moist loaf.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a moderate oven (350°).
(Children seem to like this meat loaf when they don't like others.)
Serves 12 half-inch slices.

title: hot cheesy dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with milk.
Chop beef in blender.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add garlic, white pepper, green pepper and onion.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Put in a greased baking dish and sprinkle with nuts.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sassy spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain.

title: dill pickles
directions: Option: You may add 1/4 teaspoon alum to vinegar mixture for crisper pickles.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add whole cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts. Chill until set. Makes a firm salad that stays together on the plate.
Can be made in individual molds.

title: carrots marcelle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring water with carrots and bouillon cube to a boil. Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until carrots are crisp and tender. Drain and set aside. Saut onions in butter; remove from heat and add cheese, sour cream and milk. Blend until cheese is melted. Stir in carrots and spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and parsley. Bake until heated through, approximately 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes or until tender.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: good salad
directions: In a bowl add cream cheese and jello. Stir in boiling water; stir until dissolved. Chill about 1 hr. Fold in whipped cream, marshmallows, and oranges into jello mixture. Chill until firm. Garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: chow-chow relish
directions: Chop vegetables with coarse blade.
Sprinkle vegetables with 1/2 cup salt.
Let
stand overnight.
Rinse off and drain well. Combine main ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture, heat to a boil and
simmer three minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars. Yield:
8 pints.

title: lemon cloud
directions: In medium bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with sugar.
Add boiling water; stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Stir in lemon juice and 1 teaspoon lemon peel.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Add egg whites to gelatine mixture.
With electric mixer, beat at high speed until light and fluffy, about 10 minutes.
Chill.

title: no-fat cocoa cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add water, Miracle Whip and vanilla. Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Saute chopped onion until soft. Combine with other ingredients.
Slice some cheese and cover top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, soup, eggs, cheese, onion, seasonings and 1/2 of cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs and drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.

title: low calorie hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix
all
together.
Store in airtight container.
Use 4 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.
Optional for richer mix: 1/3 cup nondairy creamer.

title: cassia bud pickles
directions: Heat water and salt to boiling; cool and add to washed cucumbers, split lengthwise.
Cover; let stand 1 week.
Drain; cover with boiling water and add alum.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and cover with hot syrup made by heating vinegar and 2 1/2 cups sugar, the celery seed and cassia buds (tied in a bag) for 3 successive days.
Drain off syrup; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Heat and pour over pickles.
On third day, drain off syrup; heat to boiling and pack pickles in hot sterilized jars.
Add boiling syrup to cover the pickles.

title: sage dressing
directions: Mix together in above order.
This is enough for 1 chicken. May be prepared the day before and stored in the refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in water 10 minutes.
Brown and drain hamburger. Add next 4 ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Put all together.
Bake in oven at 250° to 300° for 6 hours. Mash meat and stir.
Serve on bun.

title: pear pie
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, peel and coriander.
Add pears and toss.
Spoon into pie shell.
In a bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, mace and remaining sugar; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over pears.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until pears are tender.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham casserole
directions: Layer in pan potatoes, onions, peas and ham.
Pour soup over layers.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rich davis' indoor barbecued beef brisket
directions: Salt and pepper meat to taste.
In a large Dutch oven, sear meat on all sides over high heat. Reduce heat. Add water to cover. Add onion, garlic and jalapeno pepper.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Remove meat and reserve pan juices. Return brisket to pot.
Mix barbecue sauce with remaining ingredients and pour over brisket. Cover pot and bake in a preheated 250° oven for 4 hours.

title: banana wheat muffins
directions: In a bowl combine the flours, soda and salt.
In another bowl combine the mayonnaise, sugar, bananas (can add 1/2 c. chopped walnuts).
Stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill greased muffins cups 2/3 full.
Bake 350° for 20-25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 or 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks. Makes 12 large muffins.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Mix Jell-O in frozen strawberries after they are thawed.
Let stand until Jell-O is thawed.
Spread miniature marshmallows over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over marshmallows.
Pour strawberry and Jell-O mixture over cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue beef on the grill
directions: Salt and pepper roast, using a liberal amount of garlic salt. Marinate in Worcestershire sauce 24 hours or more.
Use enough Worcestershire sauce to cover meat.
You may use a plastic bag to help keep sauce in contact with meat.
Cook in covered charcoal grill for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.
Slice in 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick slices and serve hot.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix punch and Sprite together; add ice cream.

title: low cholesterol eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat enough oil to cover bottom of a large pan.
Dip eggplant slices in egg product and bread crumbs and coat well.
Fry eggplant until golden and tender.
Drain on brown paper bag.
Layer all eggplant in a baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms and tomato slices.
Pour tomato sauce evenly over top. Add slices of cheese evenly over sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and golden.

title: bake and take cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add salt, vanilla, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg to flour.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture; add oats.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° in sheet pan.

title: caramels
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a 2-quart heavy pan, over medium heat, heat all ingredients to boiling point or until sugar dissolves.
Stir often.
Cook to a firm ball stage.
Pour into pan and let cool for 30 minutes or so.
Cut and let stand for up to 2 hours.
Wrap each candy in plastic wrap.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Then add dry ingredients and lastly, chips and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage and onion until meat is brown.
Drain.
Add sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, touch of garlic salt and pepper.
Stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Chill.
Shape into small balls and coat with flour.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Dip balls into egg-milk mixture and roll into bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat to brown.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mushroom bread stuffing
directions: Saute
butter, onion and celery until tender.
Add mushrooms. Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Boil ham hocks in 2 quarts water until tender.
Cut meat from bones; replace meat in pot.
Add all ingredients except cabbage and macaroni; salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Add a little water if too thick.
Finally, add cabbage and macaroni and continue cooking until macaroni is tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ripe tomato pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients except vinegar for 1 hour. Add vinegar and mixed pickles tied in cheesecloth. Simmer an hour. Seal in hot jars.

title: b~b~q pineapple
directions: Take a fresh pineapple, cut in long pieces, core and take skin off. Put in aluminum foil. Cover with brown sugar and butter. Cook on pit until tender.

title: mrs. pitts' pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
As you continue to blend, add flour, a little at a time.
Add milk slowly, then salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Grease and flour large tube cake pan.
Fill a little over half the pan (do not fill anymore than this amount, it will cook over and down sides).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: little smokies
directions: Mix chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over sausages in crock-pot and simmer.
Serve in sauce with toothpicks.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with a little more than half the pastry.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and peaches.
Place in crust; sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with butter.
Roll remaining pastry out and use.
Can be cut into fancy shapes and placed on top of peaches.
Flute edges of pie.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and peaches are tender. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: frozen white chocolate mousse cake with raspberry sauce(8 servings)
directions: Mix crumbs and butter in medium bowl.
Press into bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate crust while preparing mousse.

title: date balls
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the sugar, egg, margarine and dates. Cook 3 to 4 minutes until dates are soft.
Remove from heat and add the pecans and Rice Krispies.
Let cool slightly.
(I put mine in cold water to speed up.)
Roll into walnuts
size balls and roll in coconut.

title: quick no-bake brownies
directions: In buttered 9-inch square pan, sprinkle 1/4 cup nuts.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Stir and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup nuts.
Chill 4 hours, or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cabbage casserole(this is a great skillet casserole dish.)
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage and drain grease.
Fry potatoes with cooked sausage and 1/2 cup water.
Add onion, cabbage, salt and pepper; simmer for 1 hour.
Add more water, if needed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chunky chicken-potato soup(lite choice)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Place half of potato mixture in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Top with cover and process until smooth.
Add pureed mixture, chicken and milk to Dutch oven. Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in pimiento. Ladle soup into serving bowls.
Top each serving with 2 teaspoons sour cream, 2 teaspoons cheese and 1 teaspoon chives.
Yields 8 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour with soda and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Place in three 9-inch greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool layers before icing.
Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread between layers.

title: quick breakfast punch
directions: Mix orange juice according to directions on can, substituting Sprite for the water.

title: chili
directions: Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of shortening in pot and melt; add meat and sear.
Keep stirring until brown.
Add tomato puree and rest of seasoning and cook 2 hours or until done.
Add water as needed.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine apples and water in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook 20 to 25 minutes, until tender. Mash.
Stir in sugars and remaining ingredients.
(Stir in the pectin before the sugar; stir to dissolve.)
Bring to boil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Brown turkey or beef with the onion. Drain.
Stir in vegetables, catsup, water, mustard and garlic powder. Cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni and cheese and season with salt and pepper.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix well.
Crumble fried bacon and sprinkle along with sliced stuffed olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with a glass dipped in the sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: crock-pot beef-barley vegetable soup
directions: In a large frying pan, brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Pour meat mixture into a crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Simmer soup on high 1 1/2 to 2 hours or more until done.

title: elvis cake
directions: Bake cake mix in
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the sugar and pineapple and let
boil
for
minutes.
Pour over cake. Combine cream
cheese,
confectioners sugar, oleo (melted) and pecans. Spread on cake.

title: rose's fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, stirring often and rapidly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the following:
chocolate squares, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Fluff and chopped walnuts (optional).
Mix well and then put on a buttered cookie sheet or a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Set chicken individually on aluminum foil square.
Sprinkle chicken breast with Mrs. Dash.
Baste 1 tablespoon or more of Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap securely.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: extra moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into greased cake pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and flatten with crisscross pattern with a fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: To make crust, combine margarine and graham cracker crumbs. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Combine eggs, 1 cup margarine and powdered sugar; blend until fluffy and spread over crust.
Spread pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill; cut into squares to serve.

title: oven rice
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour.
Stir once or twice while baking.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix boiling water with Jell-O until smooth.
Stir in strawberry soda.
Refrigerate or put in a freezer for quick set. Stir in crushed pineapple and thawed strawberries; refrigerate. Wait 15 minutes.
Whip the cream; fold in.
Pour in a large glass serving bowl.
Refrigerate!

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, water and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Place sheets of foil on countertop.
Remove cookies to cool completely.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Beat well with fork eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until pie cracks.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: travis' favorite calico beans
directions: Fry together first three ingredients.
When browned, remove from heat and drain well.
In large baking pot, mix together remaining ingredients.
Add bacon, hamburg and onion mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry dessert cake
directions: Place pie filling in ungreased 9 x 3 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in 325° oven until brown.
Do not stir this!

title: applesauce bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add applesauce, then add rest of ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost if desired.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter; set aside.
In separate container mix 2 eggs slightly beaten with vanilla and evaporated milk.
Once mixed, add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gelatin fruit punch
directions: Mix and chill ingredients, except for ginger ale, which should be added just before serving.
Serves 50.

title: herbed chicken saute
directions: Combine lemon juice, olive oil and water.
Add onion powder, basil leaves and black pepper.
Brush over boneless, skinless chicken breasts.
Saute in nonstick skillet until lightly browned and thoroughly cooked.

title: apple pastry squares
directions: In an extra large bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Add apple slices; toss to coat.
In another extra large bowl, stir together the flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in the shortening till pieces are the size of small peas.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, 6 tablespoons water, and lemon juice.
Add to flour mixture; mix till flour mixture is moistened.

title: cranberry sour cream salad
directions: Spread on top of salad.

title: tasty tater tots
directions: Spread frozen mixed vegetables in a casserole dish.
Put browned ground chuck on top.
Mix the cream of mushroom soup and 1/4 cup milk together and pour over the vegetables and meat. Place Tater Tots on top in rows.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine melted butter and crushed wafers. Pat into a 9-inch pie tin.
Melt the marshmallows, cool, then add creme de menthe, creme de cacao and whipping cream.
Pour in pie crust and place in freezer.
Can be garnished with leftover crumbs from crust. Can be made one or two days ahead, but must be kept in the freezer.
Take out of freezer about 5 to 10 minutes before serving for easier cutting. Very good.

title: homemade eagle brand
directions: Put in blender.
Mix until smooth.
Make 1 1/4 cups, same as 1 can Eagle Brand milk.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and cook 15 minutes.
Store in jar in refrigerator.

title: sweet cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients with flour, knead well.
Roll out dough, cut into shapes.
Bake at 450 degrees on greased pan until edges start to turn brown.
Do not over bake.

title: creamy mustard sauce
directions: In top part of double boiler, beat egg, mustard, sugar, butter, salt and vinegar. Set over simmering water. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, beating with whisk until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Beat in mayonnaise. Fold in whipped cream. Cover and refrigerate until needed. Sprinkle with parsley or chives before serving.

title: camping candy
directions: Mix brown sugar and corn syrup in large saucepan.
Boi for several minutes.
Blend in peanut butter.
Combine enough of the remaining ingredients to measure 6 cups in bowl, mixing well.
Mix into peanut butter mixture.
Shape into small balls.
May use 1/2 cup honey for sugar and half the corn syrup.

title: karo syrup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening with vanilla.
Add syrup and eggs. Continue beating.
Fold in half of flour, baking powder and half of milk.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Pour into two 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Karo frosting.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
In a large mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixed (hand mix only).
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on cake rack for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: joyce davis' congealed salad
directions: Let
Jell-O
chill
until
it
begins
to thicken.
Mix mashed bananas,
nuts and pineapple and add to Jell-O to whip with cream and cheese into Jell-O.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.	To make
whipping cream
more colorful, use vegetable coloring.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook 1 hour over a low flame, stirring every 10 minutes.
Mix last three ingredients in a bowl. When the first mixture has finished cooking, mix it with second mixture.
Pour combined ingredients into a dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and beat 2 minutes. Add the frosting to the batter and mix well. Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°. DELICIOUS!!!

title: carrot-cheese scallop
directions: In medium saucepan, cook carrots 5 minutes in salted water. Drain.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter and stir in flour slowly.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: molasses pecan pie
directions: Combine the eggs, molasses, corn syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix the flour with a small amount of egg mixture.
Stir into remaining egg mixture.
Add pecans.
Turn into a pastry shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 minutes or until done.
Serve cold.

title: placerville angel cake
directions: Take 1 pound soda box, cut 2 1/2 inches from the bottom; fill with sugar.
Sift sugar 7 times.
Fill "measuring box" with flour and cream of tartar, sifting 7 times.

title: frankfurter pie
directions: Brown frankfurters, onion, green peppers and celery in butter or margarine.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Pour into a greased casserole and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: steak diane
directions: Saute garlic in butter 2 minutes.
Remove.
Stir in mustard and salt.
Add steaks and brown lightly on both sides.
Remove. Stir parsley, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper into pan drippings.
Heat and then pour over steaks.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all fruits together.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
Can be frozen.
Good served with turkey or chicken dinners.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add sauce and seasoning mix. Heat well.
Line bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with 6 tortillas.
Pour meat mixture over them.
Cover with remaining tortillas.
Pour soup over top, then milk over soup and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 generously.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Heat oil and brown chicken.
Then cover and cook slowly, about 10 minutes.
Remove oil and add oil to other ingredients. Simmer until mushrooms are tender.
Return chicken and simmer covered for about 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: pumpkin pie(st. marks cookbook)
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Before baking, sprinkle cinnamon over tops.
Makes three 9-inch pies.
I make 2 deep dish pies.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk, pineapple, lemon juice together and add whipped topping.
Put into graham crust and refrigerate.

title: strawberry twinkie
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Place them, cream side down, to line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: In a small bowl, combine egg and water.
In another bowl, combine salt and potato flakes.
Dip mushrooms, one at a time, in the egg mixture.
Toss in the second mixture, adding more potato flakes as needed.
Fry in oil 2 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with garlic or onion salt.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix together and set aside in refrigerator.

title: hermits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream the sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Mix together and drop by spoonfuls.

title: lebanon nut cookies
directions: With pastry blender or 2 knives scissor-fashion, cut butter into flour.
Add about 1/4 cup water and toss quickly together, forming a smooth ball of dough.
Form dough; break off walnut-size pieces.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Make large indentation in center of each, forming little nests.

title: green beans a la peggy
directions: Saute chopped onions and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add drained green beans and 1/2 can of water.
Cook in saucepan over low heat for 1 hour.
Make the topping from melted butter, bread crumbs and pecans, stirring constantly over low heat.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle topping over heated beans, but the topping does not need to be hot when served.
Serves 4.

title: country corn chowder
directions: Fry salt pork or bacon and crumble.
Stir in onions and cook until golden.
In saucepan, cook potatoes in 2 cups water until done.
Crumble crackers in a bowl and moisten with milk and add to potatoes.
Mix corn, bacon, onions, salt and paprika.
Add to potatoes and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chloe's dad's chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 1 loaf pan.
Blend butter and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Add mashed bananas and milk to first mix.
Add dry mixed ingredients.
Add chocolate chips until well blended.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: almond roca
directions: Grind chocolate bars and nuts, separately. Butter a 9 x 13 pan and sprinkle 1/2 of nuts and 1/2 of chocolate into pan. Set aside. Melt butter and then add the 2 cups of sugar. Cook to a hard crack (300°). Remove from heat and pour hot mixture over nuts and chocolate. Then put remaining chocolate and nuts on top. Immediately cut into squares.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs.
Place in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over eggs and refrigerate.
Let stand 2 days before eating.

title: pork and beef ragout
directions: Trim excess fat from pork and beef; remove bones from pork. Cut all meat into 1-inch pieces.
Peel and cut onion into wedges. Mince garlic.
Scrape carrots and cut into 2-inch julienne slices. Clean and slice mushrooms.

title: coconut frosting(frosts a 2-layer cake)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and coconut, in top of double boiler.
Beat 1 minute.
Place over boiling water and beat until frosting stands in stiff peaks (about 7 minutes).
Remove from water; add vanilla and beat for 2 minutes.
Frost cake and sprinkle top and sides with coconut.

title: cocoa brownies(no saturated fat - no cholesterol)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Set aside. Place egg whites in large bowl.
Beat with spoon until frothy. Add Puritan oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 22 to 26 minutes.
Avoid overbaking.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: crawfish or shrimp fettuccine
directions: Melt butter and saute onions, celery and bell pepper. Cook for 10 minutes; add flour and stir. Cover and cook for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add parsley and shrimp; cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring often. Add cream, cheese and garlic. Stir to mix well and season to taste. Cook, covered, on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring often. Cook noodles and drain. Put noodles into a greased roaster and pour sauce over noodles. Mix. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fancy egg scramble
directions: In large skillet, cook Canadian bacon and onion in 3 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add eggs and scramble just until set.
Fold mushrooms and cooked eggs into Cheese Sauce.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine melted margarine, crumbs and paprika; sprinkle atop eggs.
Cover and chill.
To serve, bake, uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: citrus marinated salad
directions: Place all vegetables in large glass or ceramic bowl.
Mix orange juice, lemon juice, vinegar, paprika, salad oil, sugar and salt.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon wrapped baked water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon slices in half and wrap around 1 whole water chestnut.
Pierce with toothpick to hold in place.
Line bottom of baking dish with wrapped chestnuts.
Mix the chili sauce, brown sugar and mayo together in small bowl.
Whisk until smooth.
Pour over chestnuts and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce bran muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Beat egg.
Add applesauce and oil.
Mix in all-bran.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
(Very moist.)

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cool Whip in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm or cool with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare the corn muffin mix acccording to directions plus 1 tablespoon liquid.
Pour in a 9-inch pan or skillet and bake as directed.
Fry onion crisp, cool and crumble.
Lightly toss all chopped vegetables and bacon together, set aside.
Combine the mayonnaise and sweet pickle juice, mix well.
Cool and crumble corn bread.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased 8 x 14-inch dish at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp surprise
directions: Combine butter and flour and add milk; cook until smooth and thick.
Add salt and pepper and one half of the cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Layer asparagus, mushrooms, shrimp, pimento and noodles in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: gorp
directions: Dry seeds.
Spread in a pan.
Put in a 225° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn off.
Let seeds dry for several hours.
Cover with a mixture of 1 tablespoon salt to 1 cup water.
Bake at 425° until water evaporates.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and candies in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Add broken nut meats.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in water until potatoes and celery are done.
Blend butter and flour.
Stir into hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add milk and reheat.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer ingredients for 1 hour.
Add chipped ham and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: english toffee
directions: You must use a candy thermometer.

title: english muffin hors d'oeuvre
directions: Brown English muffins.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on browned English muffins.
Broil for a short time, until cheese is melted.
Cut into quarters and serve.

title: ratatouille quiche
directions: Line a quiche pan with the pastry and bake empty for 25 minutes at 400°.
Melt 1/2 of the butter in frying pan and cook onions for 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Transfer to quiche dish.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink. Drain. In a bowl, combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper. In an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half the potatoes, soup mixture and sausage; repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until the potatoes are tender. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Stir-fry chicken in cooking oil. Stir together juice, soy sauce and sesame oil. Add chicken to rotini, onions and pepper. Pour juice mixture (marinade) over all and refrigerate at least 1 hour, overnight is better.
Ziploc freezer bag works really well to marinate.

title: sarah's onion rings
directions: Slice onions into thin slices.
Soak in cold water.
Dump onions in flour, shake off excess.
Mix eggs with buttermilk.
Thin with water if too thick.
Dip onions into mixture and then put in cracker meal.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Drain and sprinkle with salt.

title: railroad pie
directions: Brown onion and beef in skillet until brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Turn into large casserole.
Pour corn bread topping onto top of mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour the hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Thaw 1 hour.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread over the potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry broccoli and onion in oil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soup and bring to boil.
Add Cheez Whiz and milk and cook 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven about 456 minutes; cover and continue to bake 30 minutes until cheese is brown and bubbly.
If desired, top with Ritz crackers (crushed) last 3 minutes.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in deep kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery.
Bring to a boil, cover tightly.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat; strain broth and save. Refrigerate chicken and broth at once.
When chicken is cooled, remove meat from bones; discard skin.
Cut into bite size pieces. Wash mushrooms; pat dry.
Saute in butter until golden brown. (Reserve enough to circle top of casserole.)
Measure chicken broth.
Use as part of liquid for cooking rice.
Following package for firm rice.
Combine chicken, rice and mushrooms not reserved for top in 3 1/2 or 4-quart casserole.
Blend sour cream and undiluted mushroom soup.
Toss together with chicken mixture. Arrange reserved mushrooms in circle on top of casserole.
Cover; refrigerate if desired.
(Can be baked immediately.)
To heat, bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy peanut brittle
directions: Grease two cookie sheets.
Using a 3-quart heavy-gauge saucepan, cook sugar, syrup, water and salt to 234° or to the soft ball stage.
Add raw peanuts and margarine and stir constantly; cook to 300°.
Add baking soda; stir in very well and take off heat about a half-minute into stirring.
Continue to stir until peanut brittle color.
The mixture will be a foam-like caramel color.

title: party ham ball
directions: Mix ham, onion, raisins, mayonnaise and curry powder well. Form into a ball on serving plate.
Mix cream cheese and milk well.
Ice ham ball with mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with chopped chives.
This dish must be kept refrigerated.
Better if made ahead to allow flavors to blend.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; mix together.
Bake in 2-quart casserole 1 hour or until set at 350°.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in oleo in large pan.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add soup and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in rice. Mix well.
Turn into casserole dish; bake for 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream filling for cake
directions: Combine flour and milk; mix well and then heat until mixture becomes very thick.
Put in refrigerator until it cools.
While cooling, mix shortening and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Especially good for chocolate cakes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done. Serves 8.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Using a 12-inch pizza pan, place triangles of rolls flat in pan and seal edges together.
Fold edge around pan with dough. Brown and drain sausage, then place on crust followed by potatoes, then cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute 1 stick butter, onion and celery.
Add broccoli, mushroom soup and can of water, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Stir all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook over medium heat and bring to a boil for 1 minute the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix in oatmeal, then spoon it onto wax paper by teaspoons.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter and margarine.
Beat thoroughly.
Add powdered sugar; beat well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Melt Hershey bar, chops and paraffin in double boiler.
Use toothpick to pick up balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Keep mixture warm while dipping.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, soup, cheese and water until broccoli is thawed and cheese is melted.
Add 1/2 stick butter and Minute rice.
Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashion dried apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except apples).
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Pat out layers in 9-inch cake pan.
Cover each layer and top with apples.
Makes 5 or 6 layers.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Combine first 7 ingredients in sifter and sift in mixing bowl.
Add margarine and 3/4 cup milk.
Mix well until dampened. Add eggs and remaining milk.
Mix 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 30 minutes. Cool and slice each layer into layers.

title: my chuck wagon beans
directions: Put meat, onions and garlic in pan.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add all remaining ingredients; cover and simmer over low heat for about 40 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: For pastry use your crust recipe.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Steam squash until loses hardness. Slice squash and layer in casserole.
Mix ingredients with tomato paste and slice cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruited iced tea
directions: Combine powdered tea and cold water.
Stir until powder dissolves.
Add all the ingredients and serve over ice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix ingredients well by hand or in blender on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup shredded cheese and 1/2 cup cooked ham or bacon over the top.
May be varied by adding onion or green pepper.
45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: green beans roman style
directions: Heat oil and saute garlic and onions. Discard garlic. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook for 25 minutes.

title: black walnut cake(a haunting taste)
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add
eggs, one at a time.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Set aside.
Add flour and buttermilk; mix well. Add black
walnuts.
Mix well and add walnut flavoring. Mix well. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Ice cake with Black Walnut Cake Icing.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Roll in balls, then roll in ground nuts.

title: raspberry almond shortbread thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add 1/2 teaspoon almond extract and mix. Add flour gradually. Chill, covered, for 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Make an indentation in each cookie with thumb. Fill each indentation with 1/2 teaspoon jam. Bake 14 to 18 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute and remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, flour, milk and corn. Beat well to blend. Melt oleo in a casserole. Pour into pudding mixture, reserving small amount in dish. Pour pudding mixture into dish and bake in hot oven (375°) 30 minutes or until done. If using frozen corn, add a little salt.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Mix and put all in casserole. Pour one can cream of tomato soup on top. Bake 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: springtime spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prick bottom and sides of crust.
Bake crust 10 minutes and remove from oven.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs and stir in sugar and butter.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt, then add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chips and nuts.
Pour into crust and bake 25 to 30 minutes until set.
Pie will not test done in center.
Serve warm or cool with ice cream; drizzle with topping.
You may also garnish with chocolate kisses if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into 1-inch strips and coat with seasoned flour.
Brown on all sides in butter.
Put on platter.

title: potluck surprise
directions: Cook roast until tender (3 to 4 hours).
Cut roast into small pieces.
Cut sausage into small pieces.
Dice potatoes and slice carrots.
Cook roast, Polish sausage, potatoes and carrots for about 45 minutes on medium-high.
When everything is tender, remove from heat and add sauerkraut.
Stir.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Beat together water, egg and vinegar. Add to shortening and flour mixture. Chill at least 15 minutes before using.
Touch dough as little as possible.
Roll out only once for flaky crust.

title: french toast
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 400°. (Can be done in skillet on stove top.) Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in skillet. Beat eggs lightly with fork. Stir in milk. Dip bread slices into egg-milk mixture. Saut bread in skillet at medium-high heat until browned. Turn over and brown the other side.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Pick the young tender leaves, usually lighter color, preferably the 3 leaves that are about 1 inch or so in diameter. Wash thoroughly; let it drain.
Dip leaves individually in the batter, then flour.
Place on paper towel to absorb oil.
You are ready to eat the delicious treat when it cools.
Use the chip as a dip-chip in a Ranch style or any type vegetable dip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salt water.
Take meat off bones and place in casserole dish.
Then mix and pour over chicken, the soup, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice.
Cover top with crushed potato chips and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix together softened butter, cake mix and 1/3 evaporated milk.
Divide batter in half and press half into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes and remove from oven.
Sprinkle chips over hot batter and walnuts over chips.
Pour hot caramels over walnuts. Crumble the rest of the cake batter over the
top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Brownies will harden after cooling.

title: overnight dough kolaches
directions: Crumble yeast in 1/4 cup water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Scald milk and add beaten egg yolks and let cool.
Add yeast and flour. In the morning, roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in squares and fill with filling, fruit, and pinch opposite corners forming a pocket and bake until done.

title: sunshine coffee cake
directions: Combine 1
cup of the flour and yeast in a large mixing bowl. In
a
small saucepan, heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until
warm (115° to 120°) and shortening is almost melted, stirring
constantly.
Add
to flour mixture; stir in egg and orange peel.

title: country apple pie
directions: In an unbaked pie shell, arrange the apples closely.

Mix together dry ingredients. Combine with cream and lemon juice. Pour over the apples. Sprinkle with the cinnamon sugar mixture. Place pie on a cookie sheet. Cover with foil and place in a 400° oven. After 30 minutes, remove foil.
Lower oven temperature to 375° and continue baking 30 to 40 minutes longer until apples are tender and crust is brown.
Can put crust on top, if desired.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut up chicken.
Put flour, salt, pepper and red pepper in bag.
Add chicken and coat well.
Brown chicken and sausage in Crisco and remove from skillet.
Add onions, celery, garlic and peppers to skillet and brown until wilted.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover
and
simmer about 30 minutes until chicken is tender.
Add sausage and rice to chicken.
Stir thoroughly. Add beer,
water and salt and cook until rice is cooked, about 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder in bowl.
Pour in pan with margarine.
Spoon peach cobbler on top.
Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown. This is best served warm with milk or ice cream.

title: spicy tomato cocktail(crock-pot recipe)
directions: In 4-quart crock-pot, combine all ingredients except lemon slices. Cover and cook on low setting 3 to 4 hours or high setting 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Discard celery. Ladle into cups and float a lemon half slice on each. Serves 8 (6-ounce) cups.

title: sour cream pineapple cake
directions: Stir soda into pineapple. Set aside until you get other ingredients mixed.
Pour pineapple in. Frost with glaze.
Cook in Bundt pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: quick apple tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Spread on flattened crescent roll dough. Fold corners over filling and press edges together to seal.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: hearts of palm salad
directions: Combine ingredients; let stand 1/2 hour and serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over both cereals.
Stir and add shortening and sugar while still warm so all ingredients will dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients in order given.
Raisins, dates or nuts may be added before baking.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Cover dough and store in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 6 weeks in fridge. Makes about 3 dozen muffins.

title: chocolate chip pecan mounds
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter until softened.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour and beat until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Cover and chill about 1 hour or until easy to handle. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in egg whites, then in nuts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and melted butter, then stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake near center of oven 35 to 40 minutes until filling is slightly firm.
Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken, but will become firm when cool.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar. Beat until stiff, usually 15 to 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into a 4-quart ice cream freezer.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Cut sausage into pieces and fry with garlic and onion.
Cook until half done.
Drain.
Put in a large soup pot.
Add potatoes, carrots, beans, tomato sauce and 5 to 6 cups of water.
Add spices to taste using lots of soy and Worcestershire.
Bring to a boil, cover and let simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add cabbage and celery and cook another 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage to loosen leaves.
Meanwhile, brown hamburger and onion.
Add cooked rice.
Set aside.
Remove cabbage.
Cut off leaves.
Fill each with hamburger mixture and roll.
Place in heavy pot and cover with tomato soup and water.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients (including peanuts).
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° to 375° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with fluffy white frosting topped with chopped nuts (I use Spanish peanuts).

title: pinwheels
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, sweet pickles and black olives.
Chill in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cracker crumbs, coconut and chips.
Pour milk over chips. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Press lightly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix and pour in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: spinach cheese balls
directions: Make sure spinach is squeezed out well.
Combine all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or wrap unbaked balls in wax paper and freeze until needed.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Slice onions, leave some in rings for topping casserole, chop the rest.
Lightly brown the garlic and onion in bacon drippings. Remove onion rings and save.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into casserole, top with onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: turkey oven sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir ground turkey, margarine and poultry seasoning in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until turkey is done.
Drain.
Place pita breads on bottom and about halfway up sides of ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch (they will overlap slightly in middle).
Layer turkey, tomato and celery in pitas.
Mix remaining ingredients except paprika.
Spoon over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until topping is light brown.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until done.
Mash potato in bowl well.
Gradually mash 1/2 box sugar in bowl with potato until tough.
Put some of the sugar on foil paper.
Pour mixture onto foil paper and knead dough.
Roll out with rolling pin, turning occasionally so as not to stick.
After rolled thin, spread desired amount of peanut butter.
Roll candy up like a jelly roll.
Put on plate and chill in freezer until hard enough to slice without tearing.
Must be cold.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler. Add shrimp, onion, tomatoes and jalapeno peppers. Heat for 1 hour. Add chives and bell pepper flakes. Serve in a chafing dish with crackers.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add the rest of the ingredients in the order listed.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Let cool and slice.

title: three-alarm seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in an airtight container. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: fresh blueberry crunch cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread pineapple (do not drain) over bottom of pan.
Mix 3/4 c. sugar with blueberries and spread over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit, pour butter evenly over mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. sugar over all.

title: home style bacon dressing
directions: Saute bacon slices.
Beat egg and add sugar.
Mix in flour and salt.
Blend well.
Add vinegar and milk.
Mix well.
Put in skillet with bacon.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the consistency of thin custard
Serve on lettuce, spinach or dandelion.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cut butter into sugar; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together dry ingredients; add nuts.
Combine with first mixture. Stir in apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or in 2 small loaf pans (batter is very thick).
Bake in slow oven (325°) about 1 hour.

title: bad news brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a double boiler and melt.
Combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Stir until dough holds together. Press half dough into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake crust for 6 to 8 minutes.
While still hot, sprinkle chocolate chips on crust.
Spread caramels over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle the rest of the cake mixture to cover and bake for 15 to 18 minutes more.

title: 7 layer salad(make the night before)
directions: Arrange first 7 ingredients in order given.
Spread top with mayonnaise and sprinkle with cheddar cheese.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in melted butter.
Combine soups, broth, green chilies, Tabasco sauce and chicken.
Mix well.
In large oblong pan, place a layer of cut up tortillas.
Spoon on chicken mixture. Sprinkle with a layer of cheese.
Repeat layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot.
Add about 1/3 cup water.
Cook for about 12 hours on medium.
Take fork and stir.
Add barbecue sauce and cook for about another hour.
Serve on hamburger buns as sandwiches or by itself.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all this, form into balls and put in baking dish.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In 6-quart pan, combine berries, sugar, water and cornstarch; stir to blend.
Bring to a boil; stir often.
Turn heat to low.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use large capacity microwave.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir again and microwave for 4 more minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well and microwave again for 1 minute (peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot!).
Remove dish from microwave and add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet or unbuttered nonstick cookie sheet and let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 1 pound.

title: beef-k-bobs
directions: Mix all together and pour over meat chunks (roast or steak). Marinate 2 to 3 hours, then place on skewers with vegetable or fruit chunks.
Cook on grill.

title: red potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
I leave the peeling on to add color to my dish.
Drain potatoes and cool completely.
Cut potatoes into small 1-inch chunks.
Add green onions and bacon.
Toss with enough Ranch dressing to cover potato mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: beef-n-beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until done, drain off grease.
Put meat in bottom of a 9x13 pan.
Then pour pork-n-beans over meat. Then in a medium bowl add water, brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and mix well.
Put over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 min.

title: chocolate mint spritz
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except flour.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add flour; reduce speed to low and continue beating until well mixed.
Then add mint extract to dough.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Immediately after removing cookies from oven, place 1 chocolate candy kiss on each cookie.
Makes 5 dozen.
Takes 60 minutes to prepare.

title: smoky pumpkin soup
directions: Dice bacon and cook in stockpot over medium-high heat until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain and set aside.

title: chess pie
