directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the sugar, cream cheese, 3 eggs and vanilla.
Pour over first layer.
Top with pecans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: replace eagle brand sweet milk
directions: Mix water with milk; dissolve.
Add sugar.
Cook 3 1/2 minutes in microwave at 70% power.
Use in place of Eagle Brand milk.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Thaw vegetables. While vegetables are thawing, prepare sauce in pot. Add cream of mushroom soup to pot while slowly adding Cheddar cheese to get an even mix.
Keep this at a low heat. Add vegetables to a casserole dish.
(You may wish to parboil vegetables but this is not necessary.)
Add cheese and soup sauce to vegetables.
Add browned bread crumbs in butter as topping. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots lengthwise.
Melt butter or oleo in frying pan. Then, add carrots.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and fry until brown on both sides.
Can be finished in oven if unable to watch closely.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple. Set juice aside. May need later. Mix all ingredients well. If too dry, add a small amount of pineapple juice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add oil and sugar to eggs and beat well. Add spices and zucchini to the mixture.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add these to the egg mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.

title: hot fudge sunday cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa in an ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix milk, oil and vanilla with fork with flour mixture until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over.
Bake 40 minutes.
While warm, spoon into dessert dishes and top with ice cream.
Spoon sauce from pan over each serving.

title: lemon pie or tarts
directions: Add lemonade and condensed milk to Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in shells.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freezes well.

title: grilled chicken breasts teriyaki
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Place chicken breasts in sauce mixture; cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Cook chicken on grill over medium coals, turning and basting with sauce every 5 to 7 minutes until done.
Serve with rice.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine barbecue and sweet and sour sauces; mix in meatballs (precooked).
Place in large crock-pot and cook until meatballs are hot.
One hour before serving, add peppers and pineapple chunks. Stir.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and beef.
Cook noodles and drain (not dry).
Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: benny's b.b.q. chicken pizza
directions: Generously spread BBQ sauce over pizza crust.
Sprinkle with chicken, then add
rings of onion.
Evenly cover with grated gouda and sprinkle lightly with cilantro.
Bake at 450° for
10 minutes or until cheese is melted then put under the broiler and let it brown slightly.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, gelatin and water in saucepan.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add fresh strawberries.
Pour in baked cooled pie shell.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: green chili with pork
directions: In large frying pan, brown pork.
Add remaining ingredients and 2 to 3 cups of water.
Thicken with flour to desired thickness and simmer until pork is fully cooked.
Excellent with burritos, as a dip or alone.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar, egg, honey and flavoring thoroughly.
Measure flour and sift together with soda and salt; mix well with shortening mixture.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough out to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes. Place 1 inch apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
When cool, cookies can be iced and decorated.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: raisin bread
directions: Heat evaporated milk and water until scalded, then mix in margarine, sugar and salt.
Combine whole eggs, yolks, sour cream and yeast and mix with warm milk mixture; mix well.
Make a well in the flour and pour in the liquid.
Add in raisins, walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Knead well.
Put in greased bowl and set aside to let rise.
When double in size, punch down and let rise again.
When raised again, cut into 5 loaves; let rise again. Then bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato-egg casserole
directions: Cut eggs in desired shapes and arrange around edge of greased baking dish.
Peel and slice tomatoes and place in center of baking dish.
Make a sauce of butter, flour, salt and milk; add cheese.
Stir over low heat until smooth and blended.
Pour over tomatoes and eggs.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine crab meat, shrimp, peas, rice green pepper, parsley and sour cream in bowl; toss to mix.
Pour into 2 quart casserole sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Butter a 2 1/2-quart round dish.
Layer corn, salt, pepper, cracker crumbs and cheese; dot with butter.
Repeat.
Beat the egg.
Add sugar and milk; pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover casserole the first 1/2 hour, then uncover and sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks until light and thick.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, cloves and add to eggs.
Add pecans, raisins and butter. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into mixture; do not beat.
Add vinegar as you fold.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pastry shell for 20 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and bake another 25 minutes.
Cool and serve with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven or kettle, cook beef and onion until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bacon crescents
directions: Lay crescent rolls in bottom of pan and slightly up the sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer Cheddar cheese over the rolls; can also use shredded cheese.
Fry bacon and drain.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over the cheese.
Then add the bacon; break into little pieces.
Decorate with parsley flakes.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Put all
ingredients
in a jar and shake.
Let dressing stand out for 1 1/2 days, then refrigerate.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and salad oil together until well blended and add cornmeal, salt, corn, tomatoes, olives and butter and cook slowly 15 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add eggs, milk, chili powder and sauces.
Bake in large greased casserole in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald milk and cool.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add rice, raisins and vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake, uncovered, about 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grape juice(by the jar full)
directions: Boil and wash jar lids, rings and quart jars thoroughly before canning.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the butter. Add the sour cream, creamed corn, kernel corn and muffin mix. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Add the cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: shrimp and squash casserole
directions: Parboil squash.
Set aside; drain.
Saute onions, sweet peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Add hot pepper to taste.
Add dried shrimp to squash.
Add 3 eggs, 1 cup white wine and seasoned breadcrumbs.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: outstanding popovers
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add warm milk.
Stir well.
Add flour and salt, stirring just until blended.
Pour batter into well-greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: rich banana pudding
directions: Stir 3 c. milk into pudding mix and beat until it starts to thicken. Stir in condensed milk and Cool Whip. Layer a large bowl with vanilla wafers and 3 sliced bananas. Pour in half of the pudding mixture. Repeat layers of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas, and pudding. Chill and serve. Rich and delicious!

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together ingredients.
Serve with fruit on toothpicks (banana chunks, strawberries, kiwi, apple slices, etc.).

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover pineapple with cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pie filling. Slice butter in thin slices and cover cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and keep warm. Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender. Add sausage and season to taste. Heat thoroughly.
Mix in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately over warm rice, sprinkling with remaining Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over the flour and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crunchy cottage cheese sandwiches
directions: Spread butter over 1 side of each slice of bread.
Mix cottage cheese, green pepper, pickle, chives and salt.
Spread over buttered sides of bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 open-faced sandwiches.

title: caramel pecan sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together 6 ounces cream cheese and water in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture reaches 115° to 120°, stirring occasionally.

title: quick salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a buttered dish.
Bake on 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet, cook onion, pepper and rice in oil until lightly browned. Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Combine ingredients in 8-quart pan. Bring to a boil. Stir constantly. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Stir occasionally. Process in hot water bath 30 minutes. Makes 9 to 10 pints.

title: baked french coconut pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter and milk.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: family soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water and cook until tender. Add catsup and corned beef.
Simmer until well blended.

title: vanilla icing
directions: Mix together and beat on high speed for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then continue beating until smooth and fluffy.
Crush vanilla wafers fine with a rolling pin or in food processor.
Add the vanilla wafers to the butter and sugar mixture.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: savory squash
directions: Cover and cook squast and onions in a small amount of water until squash is tender. Drain well. Combine with rice, cheese, and seasonings. Blend eggs and mayonnaise; stir into vegetable mixture. Turn into a buttered shallow 2-quart casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs. "I use Italian Style." Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Wash the tomatoes; remove the stem ends and slice.
Combine with salt and cinnamon in a saucepan and cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix the sugar and flour and add it to the tomato mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add the butter.
Cool slightly.
Line a pie pan with pastry.
Pour in the mixture.
Cover with pastry; seal the edges and cut several gashes to allow the steam to escape.
Bake in a hot oven at 435° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Make a depression in center of flour mixture.
Beat egg and water together.
Pour into center of flour mixture and work flour into the liquid with fork and then by hand to make stiff dough.
Roll out thin on floured board.
Cut part and let dry.
Can be frozen.
Cook in broth, about 1 hour.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: With mixer, cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and flavoring and mix well.
Then add cake mix. Put 1/2 of mix in pan and top with 2 teaspoons of cinnamon, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour in rest of mixture.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Tear biscuits into small pieces (about 6 pieces per biscuit). Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in Bundt pan.
When two cans of biscuits are in pan, add 1/2 of nuts and cherries. Finish the rest of the biscuits, adding the nuts and cherries along as you wish.
Top with brown sugar.
Melt margarine and pour over the top of it all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
May be pulled apart to eat or sliced.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix dry coffee and sugar in large French oven.
Add water and vanilla.
Boil slowly for 2 hours with no cover.
Let set approximately 12 hours.
Add vodka and mix well.
Bottle.
Age for a few months.

title: date kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar.
Cook in double boiler until it will stand in points when dropped from spoon. Remove from fire.
Add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Drop onto well-greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 45 minutes in a slow oven (300°).
Yields 36.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour both cans of fruit in the bottom.
Pour dry cake mix on fruit; pour margarine over top.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: curry chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Rub with salt, pepper, garlic salt, curry powder, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup on both sides.
Layer pork chops with onions and wrap; let them marinate for 2 hours. In saucepan, saute onions and brown chops and then cover with water.
Cook slowly for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
The juice from the pork chops will be a gravy that you can serve over rice.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in the bottom of a baking pan (9 x 13-inch). Pour the water evenly over the rice.
Place chicken on top of rice and water.
Put the carrots or parsnips around the chicken.
In a separate bowl, mix creamed soup with the milk until smooth.
Pour over the chicken and rice mixture.
It should look very soupy. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked fudge dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Sift sugar and cocoa together; beat into yolks, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat long and hard.
Add soft butter; again, beat long and hard.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into yolk mixture; stir in vanilla. Sift in flour.
With a large spoon, fold into mixture, along with nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch square glass baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water in slow oven (300°) for 60 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and serve, topped with ice cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grapes with cinnamon walnut cream
directions: Combine whipping cream, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Arrange grapes in a dessert bowl or individual dessert dishes.
Spoon sauce over grapes.
Sprinkle with walnuts. Serve within 30 minutes.
Good with buttery cookies or plain crisp wafer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy popcorn
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients; toss with the freshly popped popcorn.
Serve warm.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix next 6 ingredients together to make a sauce.
Reserve about 2 cups sauce and to the rest add the chicken and spoon on tortillas.
Roll up and lay in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining sauce and the final grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
Best fixed and held in refrigerator overnight.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: frozen buttermilk salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in 8 x 14-inch pan.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot except milk.
Cook, covered, for 10 to 12 hours on low (high 3 to 4 hours).
Stir in milk the last hour.

title: mary baber's sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions, pepper and garlic with ice for 3 hours and drain.
Cook vinegar, sugar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed together.
Remove garlic.
Add cucumbers, onions and pepper to vinegar and sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Can.

title: chili pie casserole
directions: Place 2 cups corn chips in a baking dish.
Cover with onion and 1/2 the cheese.
Pour chili over onion and cheese.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: boysenberry cobbler
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Boil together water, mashed berries and berries.
Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place batter in bottom.
Place berries on top.
Cover with liquid and mashed berries.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done with toothpick.
Cake will raise and be on top.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients; form small balls.
Melt shortening; brown meat balls.
Remove from heat; pour off fat. Heat chili sauce and grape jelly, stirring until blended.
Add meat balls; stir well and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with purple hull or other peas, onions, tomatoes, bell pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat process.
Top with 1 cup or less mayonnaise.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated Cheddar on top.
Refrigerate several hours or until next day.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix and make into meatballs.
Flour and fry in small amount oil until brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Use large cucumbers. Peel and slice; hollow out inside and use rings only. Soak 24 hours in lime water made from 1 c. lime and 1 gal. of water. Rinse and drain; simmer for 2 hours in a mixture of 1/2 c. vinegar, food coloring, alum, and enough water to cover. Drain. Mix cinnamon, 1 1/2 c. vinegar, sugar, and red hot candy; pour over cucumbers. Stir slowly and bring to a boil. Cook slowly until they become clear; put 4 whole cloves in each jar and seal. Good served with ham or roast. Good relish!

title: vermicelli soup
directions: Brown vermicelli in oil.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grits and cheese bake
directions: Cook quick grits 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and continue cooking over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried beef calzones
directions: Cook ground beef in 10-inch skillet, stirring frequently, until brown; drain and rinse.
Stir in remaining ingredients except baking mix and boiling water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: green pea salad
directions: Cook peas as package directs; drain well.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes with grater, also cut onion.
Put in cakes.
Fry in butter.
Season with salt.

title: grandma's date-nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Combine dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in 1 package of diced dates, nuts and water.
Drop by heaping teaspoons 1-inch apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onions until tender.
Add chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover pan and cook 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans; pour into greased 2-quart casserole and cover with thin layer of cornbread batter (thinner than for cornbread).
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stove top bread pudding
directions: Put brown sugar in top of double boiler.
Place bread on top. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over bread.
Add raisins if desired.

title: creamy chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove and strain broth.
Add carrot, onion, celery, salt and pepper to liquid.
Add 2 cups water and 2 cups of rice.
When rice is tender, add boneless chicken pieces and 2 cans chicken soup.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sift cake mix and Jell-O.
Add oil and eggs; add strawberries. Mix with mixer according to instructions on box of cake mix. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put peppers and onions through medium blade of meat grinder. Turn into a large bowl.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well and turn into a large pot.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: stacked cheese enchilada
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. To make sauce, combine the tomatoes, chili powder and cumin in a bowl. Spread 1/4 cup sauce in the bottom of a 9-inch round baking dish or pie plate; top with 1 tortilla. Spread with about 1/4 cup sauce, covering tortilla completely. Sprinkle with about 1/4 cup cheese.

Repeat with remaining tortillas, sauce and cheese, ending with cheese. Cover with foil and bake for 20 minutes. Cut into wedges; put on serving plates and pour any remaining sauce over tortilla wedges.

title: finger gelatin
directions: Prepare 30 to 40 pounds of cabbage, shred and salt 5 pounds at a time.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, granulated sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in butter.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 55 to 60 minutes until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and freeze.
Before serving, add the ginger ale.

title: babka(polish easter bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/8 cup sugar in warm water; let rise until foamy.
When cool, add yeast to mixture made by combining the warm milk to 1 1/2 cups flour.
Let rise until foamy.
While this is rising, beat the egg yolks until foamy and of thick yellow consistency.
Add the rum and oleo; beat until well mixed.
Add 1 cup sugar; beat until thick.
Add the lemon rind.
(This should be fluffy and thick; set aside.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine crust ingredients; press in pie pan.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, then water and bouillon; cook and stir until thickened and bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup sauce, chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies, pimiento and chili powder; mix well.
Dip each tortilla into remaining hot sauce to soften; fill each with equal portions of chicken mixture.
Roll up.
Arrange in greased 3-quart shallow baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Spoon remaining sauce over.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley. Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients. Pour into unbaked crust. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Layer mixture, Cheddar cheese and then Monterey Jack.
Repeat layers, ending with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with chips.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put sugar, syrup, butter, water and salt into saucepan and cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.

Continue cooking, without stirring, until syrup forms a butter ball when dropped in cold water (245 degrees on candy thermometer). Add vanilla and stir only enough to mix (you may also add food coloring). Pour over popcorn.
Wet hands and form into balls.

title: oh boy waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and shortening. Mix until smooth.
Grease waffle iron if needed.
Pour 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 cups of batter into hot iron and cook 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and chill in covered container.
Best the next day. Great with barbecue.
Keeps good in refrigerator.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown around edges.

title: green beans and rice
directions: If beans are fresh, snip the ends and cut in half.
Wash and drain, if frozen.
In a saucepan, brown meat in oil or butter. Add onion and saute.
Add beans and water to cover.
Cook in covered pot until beans and meat are tender, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Place Rice Krispies (crushed) in shallow dish.
Stir in paprika.
In 2nd dish, beat egg and milk slightly.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter.
Coat with cereal.
Place in single layer in well-greased or foil lined pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern baked possum with sweet potatoes
directions: Nail head of possum to a board just a little longer than the possum.
Skin it.
Make paste of shortening, salt and pepper and rub over entire possum.
Fill cavity with onions, garlic, chopped parsley and celery leaves.
Place possum on rack in roasting pan. Lay 5 strips of bacon across breast.
Add water and mushrooms. Leave uncovered.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (300° to 350°) until tender.
Baste every 5 minutes (this is a must).
To determine when done, pull leg away from body.
When done, throw away the possum and eat the board.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cooling rack before serving. Makes approximately 2 dozen cookies.

title: toasted almond toffee
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, water and light corn syrup.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until 300° is reached on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat immediately.
Add 1 cup chopped almonds.
Stir in quickly.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn and olives.
Chop pepper and onions.
Mix all vegetables.
Coat with salad dressing.
Let set overnight if you can so that the flavors are enhanced.

title: *shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces about the size of quarters.
Break cheese into bite size pieces.
Arrange thawed shrimp, bread and cheese in several layers in greased casserole.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Beat eggs; add mustard and salt to eggs.
Add milk to egg mixture.
Mix and pour over the casserole.
Let set for 3 hours or overnight in the refrigerator, covered.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Serves 6.

title: quiche lorrainne
directions: In blender beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard. In a 9 inch deep dish pie shell spread cheese on bottom. Sprinkle with 2 or 3 Tbls flour. Spread ham or preferred meat over cheese. Pour egg mixture over ham. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 400°.

title: potato soup(crock-pot)
directions: Chop bacon and onion.
Brown bacon and onion in skillet. Remove from pan and put in crock-pot.
Peel and cube potatoes. Put in crock-pot and add the water, salt, pepper and butter. Cook, covered, for 2 hours on low heat.
Add milk during last 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, heat blackberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water to boiling.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender, not browned.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle cheese on top and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook until it begins to boil.
Add dates.
When very thick, put in butter.
Cook, stirring occasionally until forms hard ball in water.
Pour in pecans. Let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar on wax paper.
Should make 2 rolls the size of a nickel.
Let set, then slice.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Set aside.
Beat eggs on high.
Turn mixer to medium and add the rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Pie should be slightly shaky when removed from oven.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blend all in food processor or blender.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch with cold water if you want to thicken.

title: one-dish pork chop dinner
directions: Coat pork chops in flour; reserve excess flour.
In a large Dutch oven, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Brown chops on both sides.
Season with pepper and salt if desired.
Remove and set aside.
Stir reserved flour into pan; cook and stir until a paste forms.
Gradually whisk in 1 1/2 cups apple juice; blend until smooth.
Return chops to Dutch oven; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots and remaining apple juice.
Cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Top with cabbage; cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until the chops are tender, basting occasionally with juices.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: untossed (7-layer) salad
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar over spinach and lettuce.
The mayonnaise layer should coat the top like frosting.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 8.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix first four ingredients.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt until hard-ball is formed.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Add nuts, butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy (cool).

title: philadelphia cream cheese icing
directions: Let cream cheese and butter reach room temperature.
Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cool cake of your choice.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Layer cookies, ice cream, fudge sauce and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs on top.
Place in freezer for 1 to 2 hours.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: baked chicken legs
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg, then in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in casserole; dot with butter.
Cover. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add flour, 7-Up and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Reduce to 300° for 35 minutes more or until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Then add eggs.
Make a paste of the coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add flour with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add vinegar.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans. Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Chop dates and cook in 1 cup water on low heat for 2 hours. Mash dates and add the coconut and stir well.
Add enough Rice Krispies to make a very stiff mixture.
Form into walnut size balls and roll in coconut and place on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Store in container.
(May be stored in freezer.)

title: sesame-noodle-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse well and drain.
Mix with olive oil in a bowl.
Add vegetables, vinegar and cheese.
Mix well and refrigerate until serving time.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks and continue beating.
Add sour cream, vanilla and flour. Beat until smooth.
Fold with a spoon the egg whites last. Bake in greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Melt butter in another bowl.
Dip each biscuit into butter, then sugar mixture.
Place each biscuit into deep dish baker.
Place apple slices, nuts and raisins on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: laisy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs and gradually add sugar.
Sift together baking powder, salt and flour.
Add to egg mixture with vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Add boiling milk in which butter or margarine is melted. Beat well.
Pour into two 8 x 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan(s).
Bake at 350°.
Bake 8 x 8-inch pans for 25 minutes; the 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not remove from pan.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Make corn bread per package directions.
Crumble and add pepper, tomatoes, onion and corn.
Mix Miracle Whip, mustard, French dressing and salt.
Pour over corn bread and mix. Refrigerate. Keeps well for a week.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Blend in shortening well until the size of peas.
Put water, lemon juice and egg in dry mixture; stir until damp enough to hold together.
Divide in half; makes two crusts.
Bake bottom crust 15 minutes, then pour filling into crust.
Then put top crust on and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: steak diane(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oil for five minutes at 375°.
Meanwhile, wipe steak with paper towels to remove excess moisture. Mix dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over one side of the steak and rub in.

title: peppy stuffed peppers
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Put mixture into peppers.
Place peppers in pan and pour tomato sauce over each pepper.
Add approximately 2 cups water to dish.
Cover tightly and bake in 350°
oven for 1 1/4 hours.
I use hot catsup or chili sauce to pour over top of peppers with tomato sauce for added spice.

title: eggplant with garlic sauce(szechuan style)
directions: In a small bowl, mix together the ginger, garlic, soy sauce, sugar, vinegar, cornstarch and chili pepper.
Set aside.
Heat oil in frying pan until hot.
Add eggplant and fry until soft.
Set aside and pat with paper towel to remove excess oil.
Pour out all but 1 teaspoon oil and fry meat until cooked.
Set meat aside and drain excess oil.
Heat ginger/garlic mixture in pan until near boiling.
Add eggplant and meat.
Mix together and cook 1 minute. Makes 6 servings.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix all together.
If not red, add red food coloring.

title: meltaways
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour.
Mix well; stir in nuts and chill.
After chilled, form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: steak sticks
directions: Cut steak into 6 to 8-inch strips.
Wrap each with bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Stir together mustard, juice and sugar. Brush over sticks.
Grill over hot coals about 10 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with mixture.
Remove picks and serve on toasted rolls.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Several hours ahead of serving, combine all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Garnish with tomato or pickles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat to boiling.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, vinegar and seed.
When slightly thickened, add remaining ingredients.
Mold and chill.

title: french dressing
directions: Grate onion and garlic.
Add other ingredients in the order given.
Beat well at medium speed with mixer.
Store in refrigerator in covered jar; this will keep for several weeks.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and shred. Discard core and tough ribs. Heat 3 or more tablespoons drippings in large skillet. Put in cabbage and stir until it glistens. Add salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar. Fry until tender.

title: pumpkin vegetable soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion 5 minutes in hot butter.
Add broth and heat to boiling; add vegetables, potato, celery and beans.
Then cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add pumpkin and seasoning; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Cover and reduce to low; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cream and heat through.
Serve in hollowed out pumpkin.
Can add small amount of raw pumpkin, put in with vegetables, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Mix tomato sauce and spices and pour over sausage, peppers and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil sliced carrots 5 minutes in small amount of water.
Also cook chopped onion with the carrots.
Place in casserole dish with 1/2 stick butter and cubed Velveeta.
Put a few crushed potato chips on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sandwich cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add
sugar
and	blend it.
Add eggs and milk. Stir until well mixed.
Mix baking powder and salt with flour. Combine
mixtures.	Add
vanilla.
Mix smooth.
Spread to 1/2-inch thickness	in
greased and flour-dusted cake pan. Cover with dates.
Layer
nuts over dates.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff. Add
cup
brown	sugar
to beaten egg whites. Spread over layer of nuts.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven in an 11 x 8-inch pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and place in well buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Add layer egg slices, grated cheese and soup.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: taco stew
directions: Cook ground meat, chilies and onion in a large pot until the meat has lost its pink color.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or longer.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix the pudding and milk. Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
